UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Incredible power can be found in the spirits or "muisek" of the creatures that we battle against.$B$BLook inside yourself; learn to harness the power of your own spirit, and you will be more powerful than you ever imagined.' WHERE entry=1757; /* Text0_0: Incredible power can be found in the spirits or "muisek" of the creatures that we battle against.$B$BLook inside yourself; learn to harness the power of your own spirit, and you will be more powerful than you ever imagined. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Sul\'thraze... the first time I heard the word uttered I was around your age. It meant nothing to me then, as it means nothing to you now. It was not until a warband of trolls coming from Zul\'Farrak laid waste to the land that I understood... and feared.$B$BMany will tell you that the Splitblade of Suffering does not exist. That it\'s a myth; a rumor started to scare children \'straight.\' But believe me, $r, it exists.$B$B<Trenton loses focus as he runs his hand across the jagged scar on his face.>' WHERE entry=1758; /* Text0_0: Sul\'thraze... the first time I heard the word uttered I was around your age. It meant nothing to me then, as it means nothing to you now. It was not until a warband of trolls coming from Zul\'Farrak laid waste to the land that I understood... and feared.$B$BMany will tell you that the Splitblade of Suffering does not exist. That it\'s a myth; a rumor started to scare children \'straight.\' But believe me, $r, it exists.$B$B<Trenton loses focus as he runs his hand across the jagged scar on his face.> */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Split in two to form the one. The twin blades are bound to Zul\'Farrak.$B$BSul\'thraze reborn when the twins are found.' WHERE entry=1759; /* Text0_0: Split in two to form the one. The twin blades are bound to Zul\'Farrak.$B$BSul\'thraze reborn when the twins are found. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The guards of Theramore are the finest group of Alliance soldiers based in Kalimdor. It is our duty to uphold the laws of the Alliance even so far away from our homes.' WHERE entry=1793; /* Text0_0: The guards of Theramore are the finest group of Alliance soldiers based in Kalimdor. It is our duty to uphold the laws of the Alliance even so far away from our homes. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='We don\'t know much about the burning of the Shady Rest Inn, except that James Hyal\'s wife and child were unable to escape.$b$bWe managed to drag James out, but he hasn\'t been the same since.$b$bWe have many leads but not much evidence. It is our hope that through the efforts of the guard and the vigilant help of the people of Theramore, we will unravel this terrible crime.$b$bIf you would like to lend assistance to the investigation, what remains of the inn can be found at the border to the Barrens.' WHERE entry=1794; /* Text0_0: We don\'t know much about the burning of the Shady Rest Inn, except that James Hyal\'s wife and child were unable to escape.$b$bWe managed to drag James out, but he hasn\'t been the same since.$b$bWe have many leads but not much evidence. It is our hope that through the efforts of the guard and the vigilant help of the people of Theramore, we will unravel this terrible crime.$b$bIf you would like to lend assistance to the investigation, what remains of the inn can be found at the border to the Barrens. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Can you see them, mortal? No... I did not think you could. Sighted but sightless - it is your gift and your curse.' WHERE entry=1796; /* Text0_0: Can you see them, mortal? No... I did not think you could. Sighted but sightless - it is your gift and your curse. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='In the age of war, Razelikh the Defiler served as the most fearsome of Lord Kazzak\'s lieutenants. When the Legion was defeated and Kazzak forced back into the Tainted Scar, Razelikh was tasked by his master to secure the Blasted Lands.$B$BWhile the Alliance fought petty battles with the Horde over territory outside of the Blasted Lands, Razelikh was uniting the differing Shadow Council sects and the brutish Dreadmaul ogres of the land.' WHERE entry=1813; /* Text0_0: In the age of war, Razelikh the Defiler served as the most fearsome of Lord Kazzak\'s lieutenants. When the Legion was defeated and Kazzak forced back into the Tainted Scar, Razelikh was tasked by his master to secure the Blasted Lands.$B$BWhile the Alliance fought petty battles with the Horde over territory outside of the Blasted Lands, Razelikh was uniting the differing Shadow Council sects and the brutish Dreadmaul ogres of the land. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Tragically, it was Thrall\'s wisdom that finally sealed the bond between the demon lord and his minions. It was Trebor\'s regiment that served as the catalyst to unite the demon lord, the shadowsworn sects and the ogres. The lure of nearly unlimited power and the granting of immortal shock troops to each respective leader sealed the deal in blood.$b' WHERE entry=1814; /* Text0_0: Tragically, it was Thrall\'s wisdom that finally sealed the bond between the demon lord and his minions. It was Trebor\'s regiment that served as the catalyst to unite the demon lord, the shadowsworn sects and the ogres. The lure of nearly unlimited power and the granting of immortal shock troops to each respective leader sealed the deal in blood.$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What Sevine, Allistarj, and Grol did not realize was that just as their servants were bound to the land, so would they be... You see, the price for their own immortality was also imprisonment and eternal servitude under the command of Razelikh. The cruel cunning of Razelikh had emerged the victor once again.$b' WHERE entry=1815; /* Text0_0: What Sevine, Allistarj, and Grol did not realize was that just as their servants were bound to the land, so would they be... You see, the price for their own immortality was also imprisonment and eternal servitude under the command of Razelikh. The cruel cunning of Razelikh had emerged the victor once again.$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Their minds are now tainted, $r. Yes, even more so than before. They live only to serve and protect Razelikh. The amulet fragments they each hold are the key to summoning the demon lord. What you do not understand is that none of them can be harmed through any conventional means.' WHERE entry=1816; /* Text0_0: Their minds are now tainted, $r. Yes, even more so than before. They live only to serve and protect Razelikh. The amulet fragments they each hold are the key to summoning the demon lord. What you do not understand is that none of them can be harmed through any conventional means. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Then let us pretend that you undergo the long and arduous task of creating the bane necessary to break through the demonic wards placed upon the triad. What would be your next course of action? To face the Defiler in his lair?$B$B<Loramus laughs.>$b' WHERE entry=1817; /* Text0_0: Then let us pretend that you undergo the long and arduous task of creating the bane necessary to break through the demonic wards placed upon the triad. What would be your next course of action? To face the Defiler in his lair?$B$B<Loramus laughs.>$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The humans claimed much of the Dustwallow Marsh for themselves, but the Stonemaul clan, with our help, has been able to push them back.' WHERE entry=1818; /* Text0_0: The humans claimed much of the Dustwallow Marsh for themselves, but the Stonemaul clan, with our help, has been able to push them back. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The humans built an inn on the edge of the Barrens. The Shady Rest, they called it. Weeks ago, it was burned down.$b$bThe Warchief told us to leave the humans alone, so long as they didn\'t cross our borders, but it appears someone violated his wishes.$b$bHe has put me in charge of getting to the bottom of it. If you wish to provide assistance, go to the remains of the Shady Rest Inn and return any clues you find to me.' WHERE entry=1819; /* Text0_0: The humans built an inn on the edge of the Barrens. The Shady Rest, they called it. Weeks ago, it was burned down.$b$bThe Warchief told us to leave the humans alone, so long as they didn\'t cross our borders, but it appears someone violated his wishes.$b$bHe has put me in charge of getting to the bottom of it. If you wish to provide assistance, go to the remains of the Shady Rest Inn and return any clues you find to me. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If Reethe is somehow involved with the burning of the Shady Rest Inn, you\'ll have to find him and get some answers out of him.$b$bI sent Ogron to track him down. He was headed off to the southeast, toward the main road through the marsh. Meet up with Ogron and then go find Reethe.' WHERE entry=1820; /* Text0_0: If Reethe is somehow involved with the burning of the Shady Rest Inn, you\'ll have to find him and get some answers out of him.$b$bI sent Ogron to track him down. He was headed off to the southeast, toward the main road through the marsh. Meet up with Ogron and then go find Reethe. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='I don\'t care to hear it, $N. Nope, no way are you going to be let into the Searing Gorge. Impossible. Not going to happen. How many times do I have to tell you - I can\'t let you in! Do you not speak common? Are you an orc in disguise? N-O. NO!$B$BIf I let you in, then I have to let everybody in. Pretty soon your close friends will want in, then their distant relatives, then their friends, and so on and so forth. The last time that happened... well, we won\'t talk about the last time it happened.' WHERE entry=1833; /* Text0_1: I don\'t care to hear it, $N. Nope, no way are you going to be let into the Searing Gorge. Impossible. Not going to happen. How many times do I have to tell you - I can\'t let you in! Do you not speak common? Are you an orc in disguise? N-O. NO!$B$BIf I let you in, then I have to let everybody in. Pretty soon your close friends will want in, then their distant relatives, then their friends, and so on and so forth. The last time that happened... well, we won\'t talk about the last time it happened. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Are you mad? Do you know what manner of beast inhabit that place? The worst that can happen is that we\'ll have to scoop up your remains with a shovel. We\'ve lost some good dwarves to those awful monsters.$B$BSo the answer is no. If you\'re bent on getting to the Searing Gorge, you\'ll have to find another way.' WHERE entry=1834; /* Text0_1: Are you mad? Do you know what manner of beast inhabit that place? The worst that can happen is that we\'ll have to scoop up your remains with a shovel. We\'ve lost some good dwarves to those awful monsters.$B$BSo the answer is no. If you\'re bent on getting to the Searing Gorge, you\'ll have to find another way. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='I shouldn\'t even be telling you this but if you can make it past all the critters and beasties in Badlands, you might be able to make it to Searing Gorge.$B$BYes, the Badlands. There\'s some type of back road the orcs paved near Kargath. Just goes to show you what kind of fools we\'re dealing with here! A backdoor to hell? What were they thinking?' WHERE entry=1835; /* Text0_1: I shouldn\'t even be telling you this but if you can make it past all the critters and beasties in Badlands, you might be able to make it to Searing Gorge.$B$BYes, the Badlands. There\'s some type of back road the orcs paved near Kargath. Just goes to show you what kind of fools we\'re dealing with here! A backdoor to hell? What were they thinking? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Invulnerable?' WHERE entry=1836; /* Text0_1: Invulnerable? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='You\'re a fool that should heed my warnings. No one is invulnerable. You would be wise to remember that bit of advice.' WHERE entry=1837; /* Text0_1: You\'re a fool that should heed my warnings. No one is invulnerable. You would be wise to remember that bit of advice. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='I\'ll tell you what. Since you fancy yourself the hero type, if you can make your way through the Badlands to the Searing Gorge and bring me back something to prove your heroics, I\'ll see what I can do about getting you a key.$B$BIn the southeasternmost corner of Searing Gorge is a lady almost as tough as me, Margol the Rager. Maybe you should investigate.' WHERE entry=1838; /* Text0_1: I\'ll tell you what. Since you fancy yourself the hero type, if you can make your way through the Badlands to the Searing Gorge and bring me back something to prove your heroics, I\'ll see what I can do about getting you a key.$B$BIn the southeasternmost corner of Searing Gorge is a lady almost as tough as me, Margol the Rager. Maybe you should investigate. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What can you do at an inn?$B$BWell when you stay at an inn, you rest very comfortably.  Because of this, you will become "well rested" much more quickly than you would in the wilderness.  When you are well rested, you learn more from experience.$B$BYou may also speak with any innkeeper to get a hearthstone, and can later use the hearthstone in order to quickly return to that inn.',Text0_1_loc9='What can you do at an inn?$B$BWell when you stay at an inn, you rest very comfortably.  Because of this, you will become "well rested" much more quickly than you would in the wilderness.  When you are well rested, you learn more from experience.$B$BYou may also speak with any innkeeper to get a hearthstone, and can later use the hearthstone in order to quickly return to that inn.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=1853; /* Text0_0: What can you do at an inn?$B$BWell when you stay at an inn, you rest very comfortably.  Because of this, you will become "well rested" much more quickly than you would in the wilderness.  When you are well rested, you learn more from experience.$B$BYou may also speak with any innkeeper to get a hearthstone, and can later use the hearthstone in order to quickly return to that inn. */ /* Text0_1: What can you do at an inn?$B$BWell when you stay at an inn, you rest very comfortably.  Because of this, you will become "well rested" much more quickly than you would in the wilderness.  When you are well rested, you learn more from experience.$B$BYou may also speak with any innkeeper to get a hearthstone, and can later use the hearthstone in order to quickly return to that inn. */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You are well on your way, $N.  But you still have much to learn.  The southern Barrens may be where your next lesson is found.' WHERE entry=1874; /* Text0_0: You are well on your way, $N.  But you still have much to learn.  The southern Barrens may be where your next lesson is found. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Although we call this land the Barrens, to one who knows where to look this place teems with life.' WHERE entry=1875; /* Text0_0: Although we call this land the Barrens, to one who knows where to look this place teems with life. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I sell the finest cloth and leather garb this side of the valley!' WHERE entry=1914; /* Text0_0: I sell the finest cloth and leather garb this side of the valley! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='You\'ve come further than many, $N. Respect the elements around you and you shall fare far greater than most.' WHERE entry=1916; /* Text0_1: You\'ve come further than many, $N. Respect the elements around you and you shall fare far greater than most. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The altar seems to beckon to you as if it were alive.' WHERE entry=1918; /* Text0_0: The altar seems to beckon to you as if it were alive. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Praise Elune! It has been many years since I have had visitors.' WHERE entry=1920; /* Text0_0: Praise Elune! It has been many years since I have had visitors. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='As a young night elf in Darkshore, I crossed paths with a group of unsavory individuals known as the Twilight\'s Hammer. A group of them befriended me and shamefully, I ended up eschewing my faith in Elune and embracing the vitriol of the Twilight\'s Hammer.$B$BIt was not until a vision came to me from Elune, that I woke up from the malaise that I had fallen into as a follower of the old gods.$B$BIn repentance, I began work on my prayer to Elune.' WHERE entry=1921; /* Text0_0: As a young night elf in Darkshore, I crossed paths with a group of unsavory individuals known as the Twilight\'s Hammer. A group of them befriended me and shamefully, I ended up eschewing my faith in Elune and embracing the vitriol of the Twilight\'s Hammer.$B$BIt was not until a vision came to me from Elune, that I woke up from the malaise that I had fallen into as a follower of the old gods.$B$BIn repentance, I began work on my prayer to Elune. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Etched into a tablet of pure gold was the embodiment of my remorse, shame, regret, and sorrow. Unfortunately, the Twilight\'s Hammer found the tablet and branded me a blasphemer. I was summarily executed, my prayer to Elune incomplete. I am now bound to this world as a spirit, unable to transcend to the Nether; held in this cage as a warning to all that would betray the faith of the Twilight\'s Hammer.' WHERE entry=1922; /* Text0_0: Etched into a tablet of pure gold was the embodiment of my remorse, shame, regret, and sorrow. Unfortunately, the Twilight\'s Hammer found the tablet and branded me a blasphemer. I was summarily executed, my prayer to Elune incomplete. I am now bound to this world as a spirit, unable to transcend to the Nether; held in this cage as a warning to all that would betray the faith of the Twilight\'s Hammer. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The ancient Altar of Hakkar stands silently near the entrance to the room.$B$BLooking to the balconies above it, you notice a large serpent-like statue rests on each. The statues look very much like the ones on the altar before you. They must be related in some way...',Text0_1_loc9='The ancient Altar of Hakkar stands silently near the entrance to the room.$B$BLooking to the balconies above it, you notice a large serpent-like statue rests on each. The statues look very much like the ones on the altar before you. They must be related in some way...',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=1923; /* Text0_0: The ancient Altar of Hakkar stands silently near the entrance to the room.$B$BLooking to the balconies above it, you notice a large serpent-like statue rests on each. The statues look very much like the ones on the altar before you. They must be related in some way... */ /* Text0_1: The ancient Altar of Hakkar stands silently near the entrance to the room.$B$BLooking to the balconies above it, you notice a large serpent-like statue rests on each. The statues look very much like the ones on the altar before you. They must be related in some way... */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Existing in this area are many creatures considered allies of the night elves. The elves have had access to the power within each of these creatures; it is time that the horde be allowed this same satisfaction. I have devised a way that this power can be captured and used for our benefit.$B$BDo not doubt what I tell you, $N. Help me, and you shall see that I speak truth.' WHERE entry=1924; /* Text0_0: Existing in this area are many creatures considered allies of the night elves. The elves have had access to the power within each of these creatures; it is time that the horde be allowed this same satisfaction. I have devised a way that this power can be captured and used for our benefit.$B$BDo not doubt what I tell you, $N. Help me, and you shall see that I speak truth. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If tailoring is your thing, Vizzklick will most definitely have your supplies. Take a look around, $N, and let me know if you wish to purchase something!' WHERE entry=1933; /* Text0_0: If tailoring is your thing, Vizzklick will most definitely have your supplies. Take a look around, $N, and let me know if you wish to purchase something! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Grab your things, $N! I\'ve just gotten word from Nilith Lokrav in the Searing Gorge that the Undermarket has set up operations in the heart of the Cauldron. Find Nilith Lokrav in the Searing Gorge and get the low down!' WHERE entry=1934; /* Text0_0: Grab your things, $N! I\'ve just gotten word from Nilith Lokrav in the Searing Gorge that the Undermarket has set up operations in the heart of the Cauldron. Find Nilith Lokrav in the Searing Gorge and get the low down! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='One bright light appears accross the room, then disppears. Then you notice another beam... and then another.$B$BThey seem to be showing you a pattern.',Text0_1_loc9='One bright light appears accross the room, then disppears. Then you notice another beam... and then another.$B$BThey seem to be showing you a pattern.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=1935; /* Text0_0: One bright light appears accross the room, then disppears. Then you notice another beam... and then another.$B$BThey seem to be showing you a pattern. */ /* Text0_1: One bright light appears accross the room, then disppears. Then you notice another beam... and then another.$B$BThey seem to be showing you a pattern. */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Vengeance shall be mine.' WHERE entry=1953; /* Text0_0: Vengeance shall be mine. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='My father was slain by the filth that inhabits the cauldron. My pleas for assistance to the Stormwind magistrate fell on deaf ears. Nay, they want not to admit that this part of the world even exists, let alone send their precious military in to administer justice.$B$BI seek vengeance, $r, plain and simple. Is there a more passionate cause in this world?' WHERE entry=1954; /* Text0_0: My father was slain by the filth that inhabits the cauldron. My pleas for assistance to the Stormwind magistrate fell on deaf ears. Nay, they want not to admit that this part of the world even exists, let alone send their precious military in to administer justice.$B$BI seek vengeance, $r, plain and simple. Is there a more passionate cause in this world? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='As you can see, I am but one man with a lumbering oaf of a squire. The might of the Dark Iron dwarves and the beasts held in the grip of Ragnaros would surely overwhelm me alone, but I have the utmost confidence that such a brave and ambitious adventurer such as you would have no problem handling the denizens of the cauldron. Should you choose to assist me, I shall reward you with riches and wealth beyond your wildest dreams.' WHERE entry=1955; /* Text0_0: As you can see, I am but one man with a lumbering oaf of a squire. The might of the Dark Iron dwarves and the beasts held in the grip of Ragnaros would surely overwhelm me alone, but I have the utmost confidence that such a brave and ambitious adventurer such as you would have no problem handling the denizens of the cauldron. Should you choose to assist me, I shall reward you with riches and wealth beyond your wildest dreams. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I give unto you cordial salutations, $r.  You\'ve come far off the beaten path merely to speak to someone dwelling inside a cave.  I trust there is a reason for your strange, yet not unforeseen visit here.  Yes?' WHERE entry=1973; /* Text0_0: I give unto you cordial salutations, $r.  You\'ve come far off the beaten path merely to speak to someone dwelling inside a cave.  I trust there is a reason for your strange, yet not unforeseen visit here.  Yes? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings, $Gsir:miss;. I am Master Xylem\'s apprentice Nyrill. If you have any concerns, please feel free to bring them up with the master.$B$BI will be here to serve you when you\'re ready to return down to the base of the mountain.' WHERE entry=1994; /* Text0_0: Greetings, $Gsir:miss;. I am Master Xylem\'s apprentice Nyrill. If you have any concerns, please feel free to bring them up with the master.$B$BI will be here to serve you when you\'re ready to return down to the base of the mountain. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I know who you are, $N.  Fate and forces beyond that have brought you to me for a reason, and it is one I take no pleasure in being a part of.  There are many decisions you will make in the coming times, and I hope you are wise enough to make the correct ones.$B$BBelieve me, $r, when I tell you this - there are correct choices.' WHERE entry=1995; /* Text0_0: I know who you are, $N.  Fate and forces beyond that have brought you to me for a reason, and it is one I take no pleasure in being a part of.  There are many decisions you will make in the coming times, and I hope you are wise enough to make the correct ones.$B$BBelieve me, $r, when I tell you this - there are correct choices. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You are quite inquisitive, though such inquisitiveness belies a general lack of understanding.  I say this because were you to have a definite purpose in being here, the question you ask would seem pointless. $B$BWith that, I bid you good day.' WHERE entry=1996; /* Text0_0: You are quite inquisitive, though such inquisitiveness belies a general lack of understanding.  I say this because were you to have a definite purpose in being here, the question you ask would seem pointless. $B$BWith that, I bid you good day. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You know I do, mortal; I am abandoning a fair number of pretenses here, and I recommend you do the same.$B$BYou have come here clearly because you know that what you possess, garnered from your actions within the Sunken Temple of the Atal\'al, has brought you to me for a purpose.  This purpose is to put my associate... my brother, to rest.  He is trapped within a nightmare within the Dream itself.  He cannot break free alone.' WHERE entry=1997; /* Text0_0: You know I do, mortal; I am abandoning a fair number of pretenses here, and I recommend you do the same.$B$BYou have come here clearly because you know that what you possess, garnered from your actions within the Sunken Temple of the Atal\'al, has brought you to me for a purpose.  This purpose is to put my associate... my brother, to rest.  He is trapped within a nightmare within the Dream itself.  He cannot break free alone. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The god that the Atal\'ai trolls had brought forth is to blame for this.  We destroyed the god\'s physical manifestation and sunk the temple, but the god was much stronger than even we had anticipated.  Its seed of corruption ran deep, twisting everything in its path.$B$BEranikus was charged to watch over the sunken temple to ensure that neither the simple Atal\'ai nor their god would rise again.  He was an unwitting victim of this corruption, and we in underestimating its potency.' WHERE entry=1998; /* Text0_0: The god that the Atal\'ai trolls had brought forth is to blame for this.  We destroyed the god\'s physical manifestation and sunk the temple, but the god was much stronger than even we had anticipated.  Its seed of corruption ran deep, twisting everything in its path.$B$BEranikus was charged to watch over the sunken temple to ensure that neither the simple Atal\'ai nor their god would rise again.  He was an unwitting victim of this corruption, and we in underestimating its potency. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The fact that you are here is a first step... a correct choice if you will, in aiding Ysera\'s Dragonflight.$B$BYou may be here for purely the lure of personal gain, or you may be here because you are morally compelled.  Neither reason is important on its own, but both are in fact critical to this end: The agony that Eranikus endures is what rousted me from my Dream, and it is now my charge to see his torment ended.  I now ask you to aid me in this quest.$B$B' WHERE entry=1999; /* Text0_0: The fact that you are here is a first step... a correct choice if you will, in aiding Ysera\'s Dragonflight.$B$BYou may be here for purely the lure of personal gain, or you may be here because you are morally compelled.  Neither reason is important on its own, but both are in fact critical to this end: The agony that Eranikus endures is what rousted me from my Dream, and it is now my charge to see his torment ended.  I now ask you to aid me in this quest.$B$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Interesting, interesting... I know of a druid that lives atop the hill above the Wailing Caverns, $N. She might be able to tell you more about this shard you have found.$B$BNow, I must get back to work!' WHERE entry=2013; /* Text0_0: Interesting, interesting... I know of a druid that lives atop the hill above the Wailing Caverns, $N. She might be able to tell you more about this shard you have found.$B$BNow, I must get back to work! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The days we\'ve spent here in Azshara are not among our best and most glorious, but we are still young and blood still courses through our veins--we shall find victory here. It is only a matter of time.' WHERE entry=2033; /* Text0_0: The days we\'ve spent here in Azshara are not among our best and most glorious, but we are still young and blood still courses through our veins--we shall find victory here. It is only a matter of time. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Belgrom sent us here from Orgrimmar to aid him in an unwise Alliance, but if his gamble pays off, then it will be to the great benefit of all the Horde.$B$BToo many orcs have already perished because of his desire to please women, but he still commands us, and our honor dictates we make the best of this situation.' WHERE entry=2034; /* Text0_0: Belgrom sent us here from Orgrimmar to aid him in an unwise Alliance, but if his gamble pays off, then it will be to the great benefit of all the Horde.$B$BToo many orcs have already perished because of his desire to please women, but he still commands us, and our honor dictates we make the best of this situation. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='I am not here because of honor, $N. I am here because of one orc\'s pride.$B$BIf I had not rejected Belgrom\'s offers, then I\'m sure I\'d still be in Orgrimmar taking care of real business.$B$BHis desire for women is not unknown to many of the female warriors in Durotar, but that doesn\'t stop him from being his charming self.$B$BHe\'s lucky he didn\'t pursue his desire for me much longer though--he\'d be short more than just the digits on his hands.' WHERE entry=2035; /* Text0_1: I am not here because of honor, $N. I am here because of one orc\'s pride.$B$BIf I had not rejected Belgrom\'s offers, then I\'m sure I\'d still be in Orgrimmar taking care of real business.$B$BHis desire for women is not unknown to many of the female warriors in Durotar, but that doesn\'t stop him from being his charming self.$B$BHe\'s lucky he didn\'t pursue his desire for me much longer though--he\'d be short more than just the digits on his hands. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Greetings, $N. I see you\'ve come from Orgrimmar to aid us. I\'m glad. I want to be out of this forsaken forest as quickly as possible. I\'d much rather be spending my time in Orgrimmar with a good ale.$B$BAlthough I cannot wait to hear how Belgrom talked you into coming out here.' WHERE entry=2036; /* Text0_1: Greetings, $N. I see you\'ve come from Orgrimmar to aid us. I\'m glad. I want to be out of this forsaken forest as quickly as possible. I\'d much rather be spending my time in Orgrimmar with a good ale.$B$BAlthough I cannot wait to hear how Belgrom talked you into coming out here. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What brings you to the Cenarion Circle, $N?' WHERE entry=2037; /* Text0_0: What brings you to the Cenarion Circle, $N? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I know, I know, I\'m out here in the middle of nowhere!$B$BMy home is actually in Ratchet, but after crashing my zeppelin here, I thought I might as well start the research I came here to do!' WHERE entry=2038; /* Text0_0: I know, I know, I\'m out here in the middle of nowhere!$B$BMy home is actually in Ratchet, but after crashing my zeppelin here, I thought I might as well start the research I came here to do! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='This spirit hovers over its fallen body.  Its ghostly eyes pierce through you as it gazes beyond...' WHERE entry=2039; /* Text0_0: This spirit hovers over its fallen body.  Its ghostly eyes pierce through you as it gazes beyond... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The land of Feralas has been through much, $r. The earth, the trees, the creatures; they are all changing what Feralas is and will be.$B$BThe Twin Colossals above us remain as a constant, though, throughout all that has happened here...' WHERE entry=2053; /* Text0_1: The land of Feralas has been through much, $r. The earth, the trees, the creatures; they are all changing what Feralas is and will be.$B$BThe Twin Colossals above us remain as a constant, though, throughout all that has happened here... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='To get down safely, I provide wings to those in need.' WHERE entry=2054; /* Text0_0: To get down safely, I provide wings to those in need. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well, now that you mention it, yeah, I did see something I thought was a little strange yesterday afternoon!$B$BI was running past some old troll ruins southeast of here; well, I wasn\'t really running, more like hopping... The sand\'s so hot!$B$BAnyway, so I was hopping past the ruins, when I noticed a camp set up there. Seems like a funny place to set up camp, if you ask me... I would have poked around a little more but one of those crazy big vultures chased me off.' WHERE entry=2055; /* Text0_0: Well, now that you mention it, yeah, I did see something I thought was a little strange yesterday afternoon!$B$BI was running past some old troll ruins southeast of here; well, I wasn\'t really running, more like hopping... The sand\'s so hot!$B$BAnyway, so I was hopping past the ruins, when I noticed a camp set up there. Seems like a funny place to set up camp, if you ask me... I would have poked around a little more but one of those crazy big vultures chased me off. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Thank you for saving me!$B$BI\'m a cook and an alchemist from Stormwind.  I was here looking for local herbs and recipes for my uncle Angus when these quilboar captured me.  If you hadn\'t come around, I\'m sure I\'d have ended up in their stew pot!' WHERE entry=2113; /* Text0_0: Thank you for saving me!$B$BI\'m a cook and an alchemist from Stormwind.  I was here looking for local herbs and recipes for my uncle Angus when these quilboar captured me.  If you hadn\'t come around, I\'m sure I\'d have ended up in their stew pot! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Hm... yes, I do have a recipe you might find useful.  Let me teach you!' WHERE entry=2114; /* Text0_0: Hm... yes, I do have a recipe you might find useful.  Let me teach you! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well yes, I do know a rare alchemical recipe.  Let me teach you!' WHERE entry=2115; /* Text0_0: Well yes, I do know a rare alchemical recipe.  Let me teach you! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings!  If you are here to access goblin engineering schemata, please have your goblin engineer membership card ready for verification.' WHERE entry=2133; /* Text0_0: Greetings!  If you are here to access goblin engineering schemata, please have your goblin engineer membership card ready for verification. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings!  If you are here to access gnome engineering schemata, please have your gnome engineer membership card ready for verification.' WHERE entry=2134; /* Text0_0: Greetings!  If you are here to access gnome engineering schemata, please have your gnome engineer membership card ready for verification. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Hello there $glad:lass;... the name\'s Oglethorpe and I may be responsible for one of the amazing gnomish devices you might possess!  If it blew up, then it wasn\'t me; if it made you rich though, we can discuss royalties!$B$BOh, and if you\'re from Gnomeregan, you can just take two ninety degree angles, smash them together, and start marching.  I have nothing to say to you.' WHERE entry=2135; /* Text0_0: Hello there $glad:lass;... the name\'s Oglethorpe and I may be responsible for one of the amazing gnomish devices you might possess!  If it blew up, then it wasn\'t me; if it made you rich though, we can discuss royalties!$B$BOh, and if you\'re from Gnomeregan, you can just take two ninety degree angles, smash them together, and start marching.  I have nothing to say to you. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well, if it isn\'t $N!  It\'s good to see you again; I cannot express my gratitude enough at the help that you\'ve given me and my invention work to date.$B$BWhat can I do for you today?' WHERE entry=2136; /* Text0_0: Well, if it isn\'t $N!  It\'s good to see you again; I cannot express my gratitude enough at the help that you\'ve given me and my invention work to date.$B$BWhat can I do for you today? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I am Tinkmaster Overspark, and I am the chief architect for modern gnomish engineering principles in the world today.  It is my job to ensure that the power of invention continues to shine brightest from our arclight spanners than anywhere else!$B$BAlso, if you happen to know a good schematic for radiation elimination, we just so happen to be in the market for one right about now...' WHERE entry=2137; /* Text0_0: I am Tinkmaster Overspark, and I am the chief architect for modern gnomish engineering principles in the world today.  It is my job to ensure that the power of invention continues to shine brightest from our arclight spanners than anywhere else!$B$BAlso, if you happen to know a good schematic for radiation elimination, we just so happen to be in the market for one right about now... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Let me break down a little math for you: "goblin" plus "engineering" equals KNOW HOW, baby.  Anyone who tells you otherwise simply doesn\'t know how to add.' WHERE entry=2138; /* Text0_0: Let me break down a little math for you: "goblin" plus "engineering" equals KNOW HOW, baby.  Anyone who tells you otherwise simply doesn\'t know how to add. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Through my studies, I see that defeating the god Hakkar\'s avatar has weakened him.  But the bulk of his strength remains, lurking at the far end of the Nether.$B$BYou have defeated his avatar once, $N.  Perhaps if you defeat it again you can further weaken the god so that, one day, we might face his true self.$B$BI have prepared a spell that you may use to again summon an avatar of Hakkar within the Sanctum of the Fallen God.  Do you want to confront it once again?' WHERE entry=2139; /* Text0_0: Through my studies, I see that defeating the god Hakkar\'s avatar has weakened him.  But the bulk of his strength remains, lurking at the far end of the Nether.$B$BYou have defeated his avatar once, $N.  Perhaps if you defeat it again you can further weaken the god so that, one day, we might face his true self.$B$BI have prepared a spell that you may use to again summon an avatar of Hakkar within the Sanctum of the Fallen God.  Do you want to confront it once again? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings, $c.  Though time and drink have dulled my outer senses, my inner eyes remain strong.' WHERE entry=2140; /* Text0_0: Greetings, $c.  Though time and drink have dulled my outer senses, my inner eyes remain strong. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Hello, $N. I train and care for young hippogryphs here; feel free to have a look around.' WHERE entry=2153; /* Text0_0: Hello, $N. I train and care for young hippogryphs here; feel free to have a look around. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Druids are very sensitive to the plight of all creatures of the world. When it was found that these birds were in danger, we set up a system of rescuing them from the corruption of Feralas.$B$BA gnome named Curgle Cranklehop leads the affair; she collects the eggs and has them sent here, where I care for them.$B$BWe could always use more help for our cause, $N. Maybe you should head over to Gadgetzan and look for Curgle.' WHERE entry=2154; /* Text0_0: Druids are very sensitive to the plight of all creatures of the world. When it was found that these birds were in danger, we set up a system of rescuing them from the corruption of Feralas.$B$BA gnome named Curgle Cranklehop leads the affair; she collects the eggs and has them sent here, where I care for them.$B$BWe could always use more help for our cause, $N. Maybe you should head over to Gadgetzan and look for Curgle. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Thank you, little $r!' WHERE entry=2155; /* Text0_0: Thank you, little $r! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Your talents in cooking are a little too low.  Maybe with some practice I can teach you what I know.' WHERE entry=2173; /* Text0_0: Your talents in cooking are a little too low.  Maybe with some practice I can teach you what I know. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Your skills in alchemy aren\'t yet high enough to benefit from my teachings.  Perhaps if you speak with me later...' WHERE entry=2174; /* Text0_0: Your skills in alchemy aren\'t yet high enough to benefit from my teachings.  Perhaps if you speak with me later... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The arcane only corrupts those who are weak. Even if you do not follow the path of the warlock, you would do well to remember that.' WHERE entry=2175; /* Text0_1: The arcane only corrupts those who are weak. Even if you do not follow the path of the warlock, you would do well to remember that. */
