UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='<Goretooth spits.>$B$BI am a warrior of the Horde, $N. It fills me with rage to know that our enemies sit in a fortress, less than a day\'s ride from Kargath, plotting against us.$B$BHow I long to break free from the bonds of duty and destroy them all in the name of the Warchief.$B$BAlas, we all have roles we must fulfill.$B' WHERE entry=3560; /* Text0_0: <Goretooth spits.>$B$BI am a warrior of the Horde, $N. It fills me with rage to know that our enemies sit in a fortress, less than a day\'s ride from Kargath, plotting against us.$B$BHow I long to break free from the bonds of duty and destroy them all in the name of the Warchief.$B$BAlas, we all have roles we must fulfill.$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Truly, I envy you: To battle in the name of the Horde, at the forefront of conflict. Mine is a job of command.$B$BCertainly, in my youth, I lived out the dreams that make my old age bearable. I now revel in the glory of victory, the bitter taste of defeat - all through the soldiers I command.$b' WHERE entry=3561; /* Text0_0: Truly, I envy you: To battle in the name of the Horde, at the forefront of conflict. Mine is a job of command.$B$BCertainly, in my youth, I lived out the dreams that make my old age bearable. I now revel in the glory of victory, the bitter taste of defeat - all through the soldiers I command.$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I dream, $N... oh yes, I dream. In my dreams I die a thousand times in a thousand different ways. Some would call dreams such as mine nightmares. NOT I! In dreams I die in the thick of battle. For each single death of my own, ten thousand enemies of the Horde fall before me. It is glorious!' WHERE entry=3562; /* Text0_0: I dream, $N... oh yes, I dream. In my dreams I die a thousand times in a thousand different ways. Some would call dreams such as mine nightmares. NOT I! In dreams I die in the thick of battle. For each single death of my own, ten thousand enemies of the Horde fall before me. It is glorious! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Aye, I could tell just by looking at you, $N. You remind me very much of myself as a young warrior of the Horde.$B$BYou will undoubtedly go far in life and even further in death.$B$B<Goretooth salutes.>' WHERE entry=3563; /* Text0_0: Aye, I could tell just by looking at you, $N. You remind me very much of myself as a young warrior of the Horde.$B$BYou will undoubtedly go far in life and even further in death.$B$B<Goretooth salutes.> */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='And modest too... Perhaps it is your time, then, $N.$B$BAre you prepared to enter the fortress of the Blackrock orcs? To wreak havoc? To tear asunder the foundation of the mountain citadel?' WHERE entry=3564; /* Text0_0: And modest too... Perhaps it is your time, then, $N.$B$BAre you prepared to enter the fortress of the Blackrock orcs? To wreak havoc? To tear asunder the foundation of the mountain citadel? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I did not doubt you for even one second, $N.$B$BHere are your orders, $N. I know that you will not let me down.$b' WHERE entry=3565; /* Text0_0: I did not doubt you for even one second, $N.$B$BHere are your orders, $N. I know that you will not let me down.$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Ah a visitor! Must be an adventurer, we don\'t get many tourists down this way. Grab a chair and a drink, make yourself comfortable. Say, you look like you have some meat on your bones. You thinkin about competing in the cage matches?',Text0_1_loc9='Ah a visitor! Must be an adventurer, we don\'t get many tourists down this way. Grab a chair and a drink, make yourself comfortable. Say, you look like you have some meat on your bones. You thinkin about competing in the cage matches?',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=3566; /* Text0_0: Ah a visitor! Must be an adventurer, we don\'t get many tourists down this way. Grab a chair and a drink, make yourself comfortable. Say, you look like you have some meat on your bones. You thinkin about competing in the cage matches? */ /* Text0_1: Ah a visitor! Must be an adventurer, we don\'t get many tourists down this way. Grab a chair and a drink, make yourself comfortable. Say, you look like you have some meat on your bones. You thinkin about competing in the cage matches? */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings, young $c.' WHERE entry=3573; /* Text0_0: Greetings, young $c. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Rend, son of Blackhand: Impotent chieftain of the Blackrock clan. A more stubborn bastard does not exist.$B$BAt the end of the second War, Rend and his brother, Maim, fled to find sanctuary within the mountainous stronghold of Blackrock Spire. It was there that Rend declared himself Warchief of the weakened Blackrock clan.' WHERE entry=3574; /* Text0_0: Rend, son of Blackhand: Impotent chieftain of the Blackrock clan. A more stubborn bastard does not exist.$B$BAt the end of the second War, Rend and his brother, Maim, fled to find sanctuary within the mountainous stronghold of Blackrock Spire. It was there that Rend declared himself Warchief of the weakened Blackrock clan. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Yes, young one, you need not convince me of such things, the Warchief and I have much history. Your dedication, however, is noted.$B$BAs I was saying, Rend had found a new home for his people, and I was among those who would wearily follow.$B$BFrom one conflict arose others... countless others. It was in those battles for Blackrock Spire between the Blackrock clan and the Dark Iron dwarves that my sons were both slain. It was then that I realized my time among the Blackrock clan had come to an end.' WHERE entry=3575; /* Text0_0: Yes, young one, you need not convince me of such things, the Warchief and I have much history. Your dedication, however, is noted.$B$BAs I was saying, Rend had found a new home for his people, and I was among those who would wearily follow.$B$BFrom one conflict arose others... countless others. It was in those battles for Blackrock Spire between the Blackrock clan and the Dark Iron dwarves that my sons were both slain. It was then that I realized my time among the Blackrock clan had come to an end. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I left. I would not remain with the Blackrock. No, the deaths of my children would not be in vain. I would not serve under an inept, power hungry maniac such as Rend.$B$BI took shelter in the woods of Lordaeron, living as a hermit near Hearthglen.' WHERE entry=3576; /* Text0_0: I left. I would not remain with the Blackrock. No, the deaths of my children would not be in vain. I would not serve under an inept, power hungry maniac such as Rend.$B$BI took shelter in the woods of Lordaeron, living as a hermit near Hearthglen. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='<Eitrigg laughs.>$B$BYoung one, the world has not always been in such disarray. It was a time before the Scourge had sacked the land. Before those parts of Lordaeron were known as the Plaguelands.$B$BIt was there that Thrall rescued me from death and it was then that I joined the new Horde... but I digress. This is a story for another time. Yes, another time... Perhaps...' WHERE entry=3577; /* Text0_0: <Eitrigg laughs.>$B$BYoung one, the world has not always been in such disarray. It was a time before the Scourge had sacked the land. Before those parts of Lordaeron were known as the Plaguelands.$B$BIt was there that Thrall rescued me from death and it was then that I joined the new Horde... but I digress. This is a story for another time. Yes, another time... Perhaps... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I\'m certain you will. Perhaps one day you could deliver a message to an old friend of mine. I hear he still wanders those woods.$B$B<Eitrigg bows his head for a moment, as if in prayer.>$B$BSo Rend, yes... Rend and his brother Maim ruled the Spire, in constant conflict with the Dark Iron dwarves. They managed to displace the dwarves in the upper portion of the city, but only after the dragons came and only after the death of Maim.' WHERE entry=3578; /* Text0_0: I\'m certain you will. Perhaps one day you could deliver a message to an old friend of mine. I hear he still wanders those woods.$B$B<Eitrigg bows his head for a moment, as if in prayer.>$B$BSo Rend, yes... Rend and his brother Maim ruled the Spire, in constant conflict with the Dark Iron dwarves. They managed to displace the dwarves in the upper portion of the city, but only after the dragons came and only after the death of Maim. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Indeed. Nefarian, brood of Deathwing, rules the Spire now. Rend is under the command of the dragon.$B$BIf only you could somehow manage to pass through the Halls of Ascension.$B$B<Eitrigg sighs.>$B$BAlas, only those deemed worthy by the black flight earn privilege to ascend.$b' WHERE entry=3579; /* Text0_0: Indeed. Nefarian, brood of Deathwing, rules the Spire now. Rend is under the command of the dragon.$B$BIf only you could somehow manage to pass through the Halls of Ascension.$B$B<Eitrigg sighs.>$B$BAlas, only those deemed worthy by the black flight earn privilege to ascend.$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Perhaps. Go now, young one. Seek council with the Warchief. He will surely wish to know of your discovery.' WHERE entry=3580; /* Text0_0: Perhaps. Go now, young one. Seek council with the Warchief. He will surely wish to know of your discovery. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Valley of Trials will temper even the weakest into a warrior worthy to join the Horde. Those who cannot rise to its tests will be left to bake in the scorching desert sun.' WHERE entry=3583; /* Text0_0: The Valley of Trials will temper even the weakest into a warrior worthy to join the Horde. Those who cannot rise to its tests will be left to bake in the scorching desert sun. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Hello there, $N.  I am known as Chronormu, but you may call me Chromie.  I am comfortable with such familiarity.$B$BNow - how did I know your name, you ask?  I am one of the bronze dragonflight, forever attuned to the ebb and flow of time.  You could say that we have met before.  To that end, we shall also meet again.$B$BI hope that my choice of visual demeanor does not disturb you; while I might be charged to be a sentry of sorrowful places, I choose not to drown in the sorrow of the locale.$B$B$B' WHERE entry=3584; /* Text0_1: Hello there, $N.  I am known as Chronormu, but you may call me Chromie.  I am comfortable with such familiarity.$B$BNow - how did I know your name, you ask?  I am one of the bronze dragonflight, forever attuned to the ebb and flow of time.  You could say that we have met before.  To that end, we shall also meet again.$B$BI hope that my choice of visual demeanor does not disturb you; while I might be charged to be a sentry of sorrowful places, I choose not to drown in the sorrow of the locale.$B$B$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Hello once again, $N.  I sense that the flow of time remains threatened by forces that are quite powerful indeed.  Your continued assistance is always welcomed by the bronze dragonflight.$B$BWhile the past is set in its ways, the future is always changing.  The decisions you make in the here and now help guide that change.' WHERE entry=3585; /* Text0_1: Hello once again, $N.  I sense that the flow of time remains threatened by forces that are quite powerful indeed.  Your continued assistance is always welcomed by the bronze dragonflight.$B$BWhile the past is set in its ways, the future is always changing.  The decisions you make in the here and now help guide that change. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Listen to your elders, $N. If you are strong of will and dedicated, there is no power you cannot control.' WHERE entry=3586; /* Text0_1: Listen to your elders, $N. If you are strong of will and dedicated, there is no power you cannot control. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Not all Forsaken are driven by Sylvanas\' will, $N. Some of us are driven by true power--power we earn for ourselves.' WHERE entry=3587; /* Text0_1: Not all Forsaken are driven by Sylvanas\' will, $N. Some of us are driven by true power--power we earn for ourselves. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='It... is... not... the best... time, $N. I must concen... trate.' WHERE entry=3589; /* Text0_1: It... is... not... the best... time, $N. I must concen... trate. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Your errand must mean much, $c, to draw you so deep into the marsh...' WHERE entry=3590; /* Text0_1: Your errand must mean much, $c, to draw you so deep into the marsh... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The infernal is one of the most powerful demons a warlock could hope to have at $Ghis:her; side in battle. The creature is stong, well-armored, and delivers devastating blows upon any foe. If you were to choose to put the spirit of an infernal into your weapon, you would gain some of those benefits--greater health and regeneration and the like.$B$BIf you wish to know more about felhounds, then you should speak to Wytula across from me.' WHERE entry=3591; /* Text0_1: The infernal is one of the most powerful demons a warlock could hope to have at $Ghis:her; side in battle. The creature is stong, well-armored, and delivers devastating blows upon any foe. If you were to choose to put the spirit of an infernal into your weapon, you would gain some of those benefits--greater health and regeneration and the like.$B$BIf you wish to know more about felhounds, then you should speak to Wytula across from me. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The felhound... a vicious creature indeed. It is not as physically strong as an infernal, but a wise warlock knows that brute force is not always the answer--if it was, you would have chosen the path of a warrior instead, wouldn\'t you?$B$BThe felhound draws upon the mana of its foes, using that and its quickness to overcome enemies. Its strength comes from the arcane and using that arcane power for its own ends.$B$BIf you wish to know more about infernals, then you should speak to Magaz across from me.' WHERE entry=3592; /* Text0_1: The felhound... a vicious creature indeed. It is not as physically strong as an infernal, but a wise warlock knows that brute force is not always the answer--if it was, you would have chosen the path of a warrior instead, wouldn\'t you?$B$BThe felhound draws upon the mana of its foes, using that and its quickness to overcome enemies. Its strength comes from the arcane and using that arcane power for its own ends.$B$BIf you wish to know more about infernals, then you should speak to Magaz across from me. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Have you spoken to either of my acolytes inside the tower yet, $N? We cannot complete your orb until you\'ve done one of their tasks. Speak to them now, if you\'re ready.' WHERE entry=3594; /* Text0_1: Have you spoken to either of my acolytes inside the tower yet, $N? We cannot complete your orb until you\'ve done one of their tasks. Speak to them now, if you\'re ready. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Please, help me $g brother : sister;...$B$BI will soon pass from this world, and though I suffer I know I shall not any more once I pass.  The wildlife though, my $g brother : sister;... the wildlife suffers too, and it knows no release.  I ask for your aid with my last breaths of life.' WHERE entry=3633; /* Text0_0: Please, help me $g brother : sister;...$B$BI will soon pass from this world, and though I suffer I know I shall not any more once I pass.  The wildlife though, my $g brother : sister;... the wildlife suffers too, and it knows no release.  I ask for your aid with my last breaths of life. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Yes, I speak a language you understand $r.  We are not animals, yet most of your kind continues to treat us as such!  Our differences though pale to the tragedy that has befallen this land.  Please, put aside your differences with my kind and hear my dying plea.$B$BI came to this land to mend what I could, and now that will be for naught unless you can aid me.  I ask for such aid with my last breaths of life.' WHERE entry=3634; /* Text0_0: Yes, I speak a language you understand $r.  We are not animals, yet most of your kind continues to treat us as such!  Our differences though pale to the tragedy that has befallen this land.  Please, put aside your differences with my kind and hear my dying plea.$B$BI came to this land to mend what I could, and now that will be for naught unless you can aid me.  I ask for such aid with my last breaths of life. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='"..."$B$BThe body of the tauren druid lies still and unmoving.  It would seem as though he has finally passed from this world to his promised great beyond.' WHERE entry=3635; /* Text0_0: "..."$B$BThe body of the tauren druid lies still and unmoving.  It would seem as though he has finally passed from this world to his promised great beyond. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I am an officer of the city, working in the capacity of the Undercity\'s census.  Since our liberation from the Scourge, we have tried to keep an accurate track of our city\'s populace.  Through arcane methods and sharpened mental discipline, I am able to access these records.  If you have business with me accordingly, please proceed.  You should know if you do, at any rate.' WHERE entry=3653; /* Text0_0: I am an officer of the city, working in the capacity of the Undercity\'s census.  Since our liberation from the Scourge, we have tried to keep an accurate track of our city\'s populace.  Through arcane methods and sharpened mental discipline, I am able to access these records.  If you have business with me accordingly, please proceed.  You should know if you do, at any rate. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Warchief has instructed me to study all kinds of weapons and armor. He has sent me here to the hub of both the tauren and orc cultures in the Barrens to meet as many travelers as possible, and to learn about the cultures of the Barrens.$B$BHe feels there\'s something to be learned from even the most pathetic of cultures... like the quilboar or centaur.' WHERE entry=3654; /* Text0_0: The Warchief has instructed me to study all kinds of weapons and armor. He has sent me here to the hub of both the tauren and orc cultures in the Barrens to meet as many travelers as possible, and to learn about the cultures of the Barrens.$B$BHe feels there\'s something to be learned from even the most pathetic of cultures... like the quilboar or centaur. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You! $R! Come here. <snort>$B$BTime is short, and my end <snort> is near. Mangletooth shall win; you will see. <snort>$B$BMy capture can still aid <snort> my people. The Razormane tribe is more powerful than the Bristlebacks!$B$BThe Horde looks to find out who leads the raids on their people. You <snort> shall aid Mangletooth in return for the information only I know. Mangletooth can help you! <snort> But you must help Mangletooth.' WHERE entry=3656; /* Text0_0: You! $R! Come here. <snort>$B$BTime is short, and my end <snort> is near. Mangletooth shall win; you will see. <snort>$B$BMy capture can still aid <snort> my people. The Razormane tribe is more powerful than the Bristlebacks!$B$BThe Horde looks to find out who leads the raids on their people. You <snort> shall aid Mangletooth in return for the information only I know. Mangletooth can help you! <snort> But you must help Mangletooth. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Welcome to Stormwind!  I am one of the city\'s officers, aiding the citizenry of the city through our census bureau.  If you are in need of locating someone specific, then I might be able to assist you.  Through arcane methods and sharpened mental discipline, I am able to access these records.$B$BIf you have business with me, then please proceed!' WHERE entry=3657; /* Text0_0: Welcome to Stormwind!  I am one of the city\'s officers, aiding the citizenry of the city through our census bureau.  If you are in need of locating someone specific, then I might be able to assist you.  Through arcane methods and sharpened mental discipline, I am able to access these records.$B$BIf you have business with me, then please proceed! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='My hatred is strong <snort>, but the time is right to tell you a tale, $r.$B$BLong ago a battle took place between gods. Agamaggan, our great boar god, fell to the earth after being defeated in the War of the Ancients, his blood raining down and his bones torn asunder. <snort>$B$BGreat thorns reached up out of the earth where his blood touched the ground, and his skull adorns one of the caverns to the south.' WHERE entry=3658; /* Text0_0: My hatred is strong <snort>, but the time is right to tell you a tale, $r.$B$BLong ago a battle took place between gods. Agamaggan, our great boar god, fell to the earth after being defeated in the War of the Ancients, his blood raining down and his bones torn asunder. <snort>$B$BGreat thorns reached up out of the earth where his blood touched the ground, and his skull adorns one of the caverns to the south. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Whew... I need a smoke and the touch of a fine gnomish woman - not particularly in that order!$B$BI\'ve been stuck inside the belly of that thing for months! What day is it anyway? Ah, nevermind. All that matters is that I\'m finally out.$B$BWOOO HOOO!' WHERE entry=3659; /* Text0_0: Whew... I need a smoke and the touch of a fine gnomish woman - not particularly in that order!$B$BI\'ve been stuck inside the belly of that thing for months! What day is it anyway? Ah, nevermind. All that matters is that I\'m finally out.$B$BWOOO HOOO! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='How?? Well, it\'s a long story.' WHERE entry=3660; /* Text0_0: How?? Well, it\'s a long story. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Alrighty then! So I was down at the lava pits of the Molten Span, testing out my lava suit. Everything was going great. I was even able to swim around in that stuff without suffering a single injury!$B$BSo there I am, minding my own business, doing a few backstrokes, when out of nowhere this thing swallows me up whole! Had it not been for my lava suit and built in food pellet dispenser, I would have been done for!' WHERE entry=3661; /* Text0_0: Alrighty then! So I was down at the lava pits of the Molten Span, testing out my lava suit. Everything was going great. I was even able to swim around in that stuff without suffering a single injury!$B$BSo there I am, minding my own business, doing a few backstrokes, when out of nowhere this thing swallows me up whole! Had it not been for my lava suit and built in food pellet dispenser, I would have been done for! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Say, I sense a measure of disbelief in your voice - but yes, that\'s how it happened.' WHERE entry=3662; /* Text0_0: Say, I sense a measure of disbelief in your voice - but yes, that\'s how it happened. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I\'m not out of the belly of this beast for more than two minutes and someone is already asking me about my bathroom behavior??? $G Mister:Missy;, I\'d have smacked you silly for that question had you not been the one to rescue me!$B$BAnyhow! I\'m grateful for the assistance. Maybe I can pay you back?' WHERE entry=3663; /* Text0_0: I\'m not out of the belly of this beast for more than two minutes and someone is already asking me about my bathroom behavior??? $G Mister:Missy;, I\'d have smacked you silly for that question had you not been the one to rescue me!$B$BAnyhow! I\'m grateful for the assistance. Maybe I can pay you back? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well, maybe \'pay\' isn\'t the best word to use. See, when I was stuck in the belly of that thing, I got to thinking:$B$BThis creature lives in hot, flaming magma and yet it doesn\'t take a lick of damage from the fire!$B$BIf only I could find a pristine hide from one of these beasts. I could take it back to my dear friend, Malyfous Darkhammer, in Everlook. If anyone could do anything with the hide of a beast like this, it would be him. $b' WHERE entry=3664; /* Text0_0: Well, maybe \'pay\' isn\'t the best word to use. See, when I was stuck in the belly of that thing, I got to thinking:$B$BThis creature lives in hot, flaming magma and yet it doesn\'t take a lick of damage from the fire!$B$BIf only I could find a pristine hide from one of these beasts. I could take it back to my dear friend, Malyfous Darkhammer, in Everlook. If anyone could do anything with the hide of a beast like this, it would be him. $b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='So how about you deliver a message for me?' WHERE entry=3665; /* Text0_0: So how about you deliver a message for me? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Wanna buy a cockroach?' WHERE entry=3666; /* Text0_0: Wanna buy a cockroach? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Time is running out for me... for us all...'Text1_1_loc9='I have so much to do... so much before the plague comes...$B' WHERE entry=3668; /* Text0_1: Time is running out for me... for us all... */ /* Text1_1: I have so much to do... so much before the plague comes...$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text2_1_loc9='John, honey, where are you?'Text3_1_loc9='What is happening to everyone?  I feel... cold...' WHERE entry=3668; /* Text2_1: John, honey, where are you? */ /* Text3_1: What is happening to everyone?  I feel... cold... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text4_1_loc9='Shhh... do you smell something?' WHERE entry=3668; /* Text4_1: Shhh... do you smell something? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The spirit looks upon you with a sense of completeness and cognizance that had not been present before.$B$BI feel as though a great burden has been lifted from my soul.  Soon I will rest forever in peace.  I now know this, and I await this time patiently.$B$BThank you, stranger.' WHERE entry=3669; /* Text0_1: The spirit looks upon you with a sense of completeness and cognizance that had not been present before.$B$BI feel as though a great burden has been lifted from my soul.  Soon I will rest forever in peace.  I now know this, and I await this time patiently.$B$BThank you, stranger. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You have <snort> aided Mangletooth more than I would have dreamed, $r.$B$BThank you.$B$BAs long as I remain a captive here, you may bring me blood shards from the Bristleback quilboar and I will bless you with Agamaggan\'s power.' WHERE entry=3670; /* Text0_0: You have <snort> aided Mangletooth more than I would have dreamed, $r.$B$BThank you.$B$BAs long as I remain a captive here, you may bring me blood shards from the Bristleback quilboar and I will bless you with Agamaggan\'s power. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Thorium Brotherhood does not waste time on ants. Be gone!' WHERE entry=3673; /* Text0_0: The Thorium Brotherhood does not waste time on ants. Be gone! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='It\'s a simple process for a craftsman of my caliber.$B$BThe most difficult aspect of crafting items out of beast hides and carapace is the actual acquisition of said parts. Now, if you could bring me a pristine hide from this beast, I could make several different powerful items from the flesh.' WHERE entry=3674; /* Text0_0: It\'s a simple process for a craftsman of my caliber.$B$BThe most difficult aspect of crafting items out of beast hides and carapace is the actual acquisition of said parts. Now, if you could bring me a pristine hide from this beast, I could make several different powerful items from the flesh. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I reckon that the odds of obtaining such a piece would be a one in a million! A once in a lifetime skin! Even the most disciplined artisans of the craft would no doubt fail several hundred times in the process of skinning the beast before a pristine sample was recovered.$b' WHERE entry=3675; /* Text0_0: I reckon that the odds of obtaining such a piece would be a one in a million! A once in a lifetime skin! Even the most disciplined artisans of the craft would no doubt fail several hundred times in the process of skinning the beast before a pristine sample was recovered.$b */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If you actually brought me the hide of the beast? Well... Let me show you...' WHERE entry=3676; /* Text0_0: If you actually brought me the hide of the beast? Well... Let me show you... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Thorium Brotherhood Fall Catalogue:$B$BInside you will find the hottest deals on all of your adventuring needs! We\'ll even show you where to pick up those difficult to find components and supplies.' WHERE entry=3677; /* Text0_0: The Thorium Brotherhood Fall Catalogue:$B$BInside you will find the hottest deals on all of your adventuring needs! We\'ll even show you where to pick up those difficult to find components and supplies. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The title of this book reads with a handwritten flourish: Maureen Dalson\'s Diary.' WHERE entry=3693; /* Text0_0: The title of this book reads with a handwritten flourish: Maureen Dalson\'s Diary. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='A diary with yellowing pages lies open to the last entry:$B$B"I don\'t know what\'s going to happen now that Harold\'s turned.  It took everything out of me to drag him into the only place I could find that\'d lock him up tight and hold him.  I hid the key on me, and I pray it works...$B$BI hope I can get out of here, but I need money to do that.  Our stuff\'s all in the cabinet I think... and now that I think about it, doesn\'t Harold keep the key on him?$B$BI\'ll rest on it, I\'m dead tired now."' WHERE entry=3694; /* Text0_0: A diary with yellowing pages lies open to the last entry:$B$B"I don\'t know what\'s going to happen now that Harold\'s turned.  It took everything out of me to drag him into the only place I could find that\'d lock him up tight and hold him.  I hid the key on me, and I pray it works...$B$BI hope I can get out of here, but I need money to do that.  Our stuff\'s all in the cabinet I think... and now that I think about it, doesn\'t Harold keep the key on him?$B$BI\'ll rest on it, I\'m dead tired now." */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What have you got there, $N?$B$B<Malyfous points to the unfired plate gauntlets hanging out of your pack.>' WHERE entry=3734; /* Text0_0: What have you got there, $N?$B$B<Malyfous points to the unfired plate gauntlets hanging out of your pack.> */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Welcome to the front lines, $c.  While politicians may connive and scheme amongst themselves, they\'ll find no such luxury afforded to them here.  This is the Bulwark, and we fight for our continued survival on a daily basis here.$B$BIf you\'ve come here looking for a chance to prove yourself as a hero, then you\'ll find plenty of opportunities to do so... especially as we push towards Andorhal and whatever malign force that controls the Scourge there.' WHERE entry=3753; /* Text0_0: Welcome to the front lines, $c.  While politicians may connive and scheme amongst themselves, they\'ll find no such luxury afforded to them here.  This is the Bulwark, and we fight for our continued survival on a daily basis here.$B$BIf you\'ve come here looking for a chance to prove yourself as a hero, then you\'ll find plenty of opportunities to do so... especially as we push towards Andorhal and whatever malign force that controls the Scourge there. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Welcome to the front lines, $c.  The Kingdom of Stormwind, with the aid of its allies, has sent me here to counter the growing threat of the Scourge.  Here at Chillwind Camp, we fight for our continued survival on a daily basis.$B$BIf you\'ve come here looking for a chance to prove yourself as a hero, then you\'ll find plenty of opportunities to do so... especially as we push towards Andorhal and whatever malign force that controls the Scourge there.' WHERE entry=3754; /* Text0_0: Welcome to the front lines, $c.  The Kingdom of Stormwind, with the aid of its allies, has sent me here to counter the growing threat of the Scourge.  Here at Chillwind Camp, we fight for our continued survival on a daily basis.$B$BIf you\'ve come here looking for a chance to prove yourself as a hero, then you\'ll find plenty of opportunities to do so... especially as we push towards Andorhal and whatever malign force that controls the Scourge there. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='It is good to see others who fight the Scourge in Stratholme, for it is here they are strongest.$B$BGreetings.  I am Aurius.  I was once a paladin of the Silver Hand, but like others whose faith wavered... I fell from grace.  The Scourge seduced me and nearly transformed me into a death knight!$B$BFinally sensing my peril, I fled to this chapel.  It is a sacred place, where the first paladin, Uther the Lightbringer, was ordained into the order of the Silver Hand.' WHERE entry=3755; /* Text0_0: It is good to see others who fight the Scourge in Stratholme, for it is here they are strongest.$B$BGreetings.  I am Aurius.  I was once a paladin of the Silver Hand, but like others whose faith wavered... I fell from grace.  The Scourge seduced me and nearly transformed me into a death knight!$B$BFinally sensing my peril, I fled to this chapel.  It is a sacred place, where the first paladin, Uther the Lightbringer, was ordained into the order of the Silver Hand. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I do not have much time in this world, but Light willing, it is time enough to fulfill my destiny.  When you face Baron Rivendare, I will be with you.' WHERE entry=3756; /* Text0_0: I do not have much time in this world, but Light willing, it is time enough to fulfill my destiny.  When you face Baron Rivendare, I will be with you. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Leave me.  My wounds are great and I fear they will overtake me.  Thank you, $N.  I will die here, but because of you... I\'ll die in peace.' WHERE entry=3757; /* Text0_0: Leave me.  My wounds are great and I fear they will overtake me.  Thank you, $N.  I will die here, but because of you... I\'ll die in peace. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Test not my patience, mortal.' WHERE entry=3758; /* Text0_0: Test not my patience, mortal. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Bite your tongue, $r, lest I rip it from your skull case and use it as a horn warmer.' WHERE entry=3759; /* Text0_0: Bite your tongue, $r, lest I rip it from your skull case and use it as a horn warmer. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What it is that I do, of course. I brood. I lament. I hate. I plot. When that cycle is complete, I brood again. What is it you want from me? I have much on my mind.' WHERE entry=3760; /* Text0_0: What it is that I do, of course. I brood. I lament. I hate. I plot. When that cycle is complete, I brood again. What is it you want from me? I have much on my mind. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You?$B$B<Lorax laughs.>$B$BThat is doubtful.$B$BI stand in these ruins and dream. Dream of the day that I catch that miserable thief, Goraluk Anvilcrack.$B$BWe had a deal, him and I. A deal that he broke. Betrayed.' WHERE entry=3761; /* Text0_0: You?$B$B<Lorax laughs.>$B$BThat is doubtful.$B$BI stand in these ruins and dream. Dream of the day that I catch that miserable thief, Goraluk Anvilcrack.$B$BWe had a deal, him and I. A deal that he broke. Betrayed. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I would teach him how to demon forge in exchange for his soul. The soul of a Blackrock orc is worth very little but in these trying times, a soul, any soul, is better than none at all.' WHERE entry=3762; /* Text0_0: I would teach him how to demon forge in exchange for his soul. The soul of a Blackrock orc is worth very little but in these trying times, a soul, any soul, is better than none at all. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='He took the unforged rune covered breastplate, used in the making of the demon forged breastplate and ran away without making payment. A fool, I am not, however... the unforged chest piece is useless without knowledge or the recipe to apply said knowledge.$B$BI wonder... does he sit safely in his city of Blackrock Spire and attempt to create the item from the raw material? I know he dare not leave!' WHERE entry=3763; /* Text0_0: He took the unforged rune covered breastplate, used in the making of the demon forged breastplate and ran away without making payment. A fool, I am not, however... the unforged chest piece is useless without knowledge or the recipe to apply said knowledge.$B$BI wonder... does he sit safely in his city of Blackrock Spire and attempt to create the item from the raw material? I know he dare not leave! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Since we\'ve begun our stay in the crater, Dadanga\'s taken a liking to the large bloodpetal sprouts that grow all over the place here.$B$BI\'m sure she\'d enjoy a snack, if you feel like bringing her some...' WHERE entry=3793; /* Text0_1: Since we\'ve begun our stay in the crater, Dadanga\'s taken a liking to the large bloodpetal sprouts that grow all over the place here.$B$BI\'m sure she\'d enjoy a snack, if you feel like bringing her some... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Heya mon.  Go talk to mah Master Gadrin right over there.  Take care of that Zalazane crazy for him and I fix ya right up!' WHERE entry=3794; /* Text0_0: Heya mon.  Go talk to mah Master Gadrin right over there.  Take care of that Zalazane crazy for him and I fix ya right up! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Ya mon, I be Gadrin\'s assistant.  Dis here volunteer work be my way of gettin through Witch Doctor School.  Since you help him, I help ya for free.  Whatcha need fixin?' WHERE entry=3795; /* Text0_0: Ya mon, I be Gadrin\'s assistant.  Dis here volunteer work be my way of gettin through Witch Doctor School.  Since you help him, I help ya for free.  Whatcha need fixin? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I... I am badly injured...' WHERE entry=3797; /* Text0_0: I... I am badly injured... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Listen, $r. Listen well...$B$BThe dragon riders came in the night, mounted atop the black flight. They struck fast and with deadly precision, taking young whelps - such as me - and escaping under the veil of darkness.$B$BI watched in horror as they used my brothers and sisters in their experiments. From our essence would be created the chromatic flight.' WHERE entry=3798; /* Text0_0: Listen, $r. Listen well...$B$BThe dragon riders came in the night, mounted atop the black flight. They struck fast and with deadly precision, taking young whelps - such as me - and escaping under the veil of darkness.$B$BI watched in horror as they used my brothers and sisters in their experiments. From our essence would be created the chromatic flight. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Nefarian had ordered that unsuitable subjects be destroyed immediately, but these retched beasts would not do so without first inflicting an \'ample\' amount of torture.$B$BWhen we were thoroughly \'broken,\' they would round up what remained and throw us to these thugs. Our bodies used as instruments in their sick game: thrown into the lava or worse; to the open and waiting arms of the bloodthirsty legion below.' WHERE entry=3799; /* Text0_0: Nefarian had ordered that unsuitable subjects be destroyed immediately, but these retched beasts would not do so without first inflicting an \'ample\' amount of torture.$B$BWhen we were thoroughly \'broken,\' they would round up what remained and throw us to these thugs. Our bodies used as instruments in their sick game: thrown into the lava or worse; to the open and waiting arms of the bloodthirsty legion below. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You came along just as they were about to throw me to the fiends below - for that, I thank you. Perhaps, I - rather - we, of the blue flight, can assist you further?$B$BYou have come this far, $r, risked much. Will you go a ways further to battle Nefarian and his legion of Blackrock?' WHERE entry=3800; /* Text0_0: You came along just as they were about to throw me to the fiends below - for that, I thank you. Perhaps, I - rather - we, of the blue flight, can assist you further?$B$BYou have come this far, $r, risked much. Will you go a ways further to battle Nefarian and his legion of Blackrock? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If you are here to hunt dragons, be my guest.  Where should I send my condolences?' WHERE entry=3801; /* Text0_0: If you are here to hunt dragons, be my guest.  Where should I send my condolences? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Your stench will attract every dragon for miles.  Tell me what you want, and quickly.' WHERE entry=3802; /* Text0_0: Your stench will attract every dragon for miles.  Tell me what you want, and quickly. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The spirits told me you would come, that you would seek me for some reason, but that even you may not know that reason. So, do you know why you are here?' WHERE entry=3803; /* Text0_0: The spirits told me you would come, that you would seek me for some reason, but that even you may not know that reason. So, do you know why you are here? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Oh hi! My name\'s Sarah. What can I do for you?' WHERE entry=3804; /* Text0_1: Oh hi! My name\'s Sarah. What can I do for you? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The forest told me of your presence, but not why you were here. So, speak and enlighten me.' WHERE entry=3805; /* Text0_1: The forest told me of your presence, but not why you were here. So, speak and enlighten me. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='How you doin\' mon!' WHERE entry=3806; /* Text0_0: How you doin\' mon! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='I welcome you, $N. And the Emerald Circle welcomes you.$B$BHopefully together we can help rejuventate and protect this once-mighty forest. Many forces seek to destroy it from without... and within.$B$BDo not be persuaded by the power here--it will only corrupt you, like it has this entire land.' WHERE entry=3807; /* Text0_1: I welcome you, $N. And the Emerald Circle welcomes you.$B$BHopefully together we can help rejuventate and protect this once-mighty forest. Many forces seek to destroy it from without... and within.$B$BDo not be persuaded by the power here--it will only corrupt you, like it has this entire land. */
