UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Just a few more and our stables will be overflowing with mounts. Release it into my custody, soldier. I\'ll take it from here.' WHERE entry=6317; /* Text0_1: Just a few more and our stables will be overflowing with mounts. Release it into my custody, soldier. I\'ll take it from here. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well met, $N. We must be brief because there is much to do.' WHERE entry=6333; /* Text0_0: Well met, $N. We must be brief because there is much to do. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='May Cenarius guide you, $c.$B$BI am here in this corrupt land with my sisters on a mission of great importance to the Cenarian Circle. But only those who are powerful enough I ask speak to me about such matters--to send a lesser being would be folly.' WHERE entry=6334; /* Text0_0: May Cenarius guide you, $c.$B$BI am here in this corrupt land with my sisters on a mission of great importance to the Cenarian Circle. But only those who are powerful enough I ask speak to me about such matters--to send a lesser being would be folly. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='My sisters and I have come down from the Stonetalon Mountains to put to rest a tragedy from ages past. Unfortunately, we are not powerful enough to accomplish our goals on our own and now seek mortals such as yourself to aid us.$B$BIf you are powerful enough, then we have much to discuss, $c. If you are not, then, for your safety, I will leave the details of my mission out of our conversation.' WHERE entry=6335; /* Text0_1: My sisters and I have come down from the Stonetalon Mountains to put to rest a tragedy from ages past. Unfortunately, we are not powerful enough to accomplish our goals on our own and now seek mortals such as yourself to aid us.$B$BIf you are powerful enough, then we have much to discuss, $c. If you are not, then, for your safety, I will leave the details of my mission out of our conversation. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I greet you, $r.' WHERE entry=6336; /* Text0_0: I greet you, $r. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I need no home to know I still have a place in this world, $c. The tribes will see... all of them. They fight amongst one another, and for what? Scraps left over by vultures... lands infested by the Legion... bah!$B$BThe centaur should be proud of their heritage--it is just as noble as any Night elf\'s or orc\'s--it is time we started acting like it!' WHERE entry=6353; /* Text0_0: I need no home to know I still have a place in this world, $c. The tribes will see... all of them. They fight amongst one another, and for what? Scraps left over by vultures... lands infested by the Legion... bah!$B$BThe centaur should be proud of their heritage--it is just as noble as any Night elf\'s or orc\'s--it is time we started acting like it! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='At last, I am free of the corruption that once bound me to this place...' WHERE entry=6354; /* Text0_0: At last, I am free of the corruption that once bound me to this place... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Thank you for what you have done, $N.$B$BKeep the scepter safe; may it aid you in your toil against the evils that have invaded this place...' WHERE entry=6373; /* Text0_0: Thank you for what you have done, $N.$B$BKeep the scepter safe; may it aid you in your toil against the evils that have invaded this place... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='My scepter... After so many years... You have recovered it! You shall truly be the savior of this place...$B$BPlease listen to me carefully, $N. The head and the rod of the scepter may only be reunited into one at the Stone of Maraudon.' WHERE entry=6375; /* Text0_0: My scepter... After so many years... You have recovered it! You shall truly be the savior of this place...$B$BPlease listen to me carefully, $N. The head and the rod of the scepter may only be reunited into one at the Stone of Maraudon. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Between the colors, a path.$B$BBlink across in light.$B$BFrom the water, you emerge.' WHERE entry=6377; /* Text0_0: Between the colors, a path.$B$BBlink across in light.$B$BFrom the water, you emerge. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Between the orange and the purple passageways near the doors to Maraudon, you will find a third path.$B$BThe scepter you hold in your hands is the key.' WHERE entry=6378; /* Text0_0: Between the orange and the purple passageways near the doors to Maraudon, you will find a third path.$B$BThe scepter you hold in your hands is the key. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I grow weary...$B$BFrom here, you can see the waterfalls, $n...The scepter grants you the power to travel to this very place, should you ever desire to enter through the front gates of Maraudon again.$B$BNear the entrance to Maraudon, you will find a passage that goes down beneath the caverns. Use the scepter at the ancient ritual site to create a portal, and you will find yourself here once more.' WHERE entry=6379; /* Text0_0: I grow weary...$B$BFrom here, you can see the waterfalls, $n...The scepter grants you the power to travel to this very place, should you ever desire to enter through the front gates of Maraudon again.$B$BNear the entrance to Maraudon, you will find a passage that goes down beneath the caverns. Use the scepter at the ancient ritual site to create a portal, and you will find yourself here once more. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Long ago, my dryad sisters and I entered these caves to free the tortured spirit of my uncle, Zaetar. However, the corruption that had already spread through these caverns soon overcame us, and we too fell.$B$BWe were destined to wander these passages; the toxins poisoning our minds...$B$BAlthough my spirit may now be at rest, I know that I have failed in my mission. It is a great sadness I must bear...' WHERE entry=6380; /* Text0_0: Long ago, my dryad sisters and I entered these caves to free the tortured spirit of my uncle, Zaetar. However, the corruption that had already spread through these caverns soon overcame us, and we too fell.$B$BWe were destined to wander these passages; the toxins poisoning our minds...$B$BAlthough my spirit may now be at rest, I know that I have failed in my mission. It is a great sadness I must bear... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Ah, Zaetar... <Celebras looks away.>$B$BMy father, Remulos, tried to stop him...$B$BZaetar was headstrong, and when he fell for an earthen elemental princess, my father knew that their union was cursed, but Zaetar refused to listen.$B$BThe centaur are the result of his mistake. They were born misshapen and hateful; my uncle Zaetar was killed by his own kin...$B$BThe evil princess, Theradras, still guards his remains here in the crystal caverns.' WHERE entry=6381; /* Text0_0: Ah, Zaetar... <Celebras looks away.>$B$BMy father, Remulos, tried to stop him...$B$BZaetar was headstrong, and when he fell for an earthen elemental princess, my father knew that their union was cursed, but Zaetar refused to listen.$B$BThe centaur are the result of his mistake. They were born misshapen and hateful; my uncle Zaetar was killed by his own kin...$B$BThe evil princess, Theradras, still guards his remains here in the crystal caverns. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Welcome to the Explorers\' League.  If you need information, and it is in book form, then I might be able to help you out.' WHERE entry=6383; /* Text0_0: Welcome to the Explorers\' League.  If you need information, and it is in book form, then I might be able to help you out. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='As the toxins lurking within Maraudon seeped into my mind, I began to lose my grip on reality. Worried that it would be used for evil, my dryad sisters secretly took the scepter from me, breaking it into two parts and hiding it within the caverns.$B$BSoon they fell victim to the madness as well, and the two parts of the scepter, left unguarded, came to be in the possession of Vyletongue, himself. The satyr entrusted one part to Noxxion, an evil elemental, and the other he still has to this day.' WHERE entry=6384; /* Text0_0: As the toxins lurking within Maraudon seeped into my mind, I began to lose my grip on reality. Worried that it would be used for evil, my dryad sisters secretly took the scepter from me, breaking it into two parts and hiding it within the caverns.$B$BSoon they fell victim to the madness as well, and the two parts of the scepter, left unguarded, came to be in the possession of Vyletongue, himself. The satyr entrusted one part to Noxxion, an evil elemental, and the other he still has to this day. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Without knowledge of the incantations required to unite the two parts, Lord Vyletongue was unable to use the scepter. However, now that I am free of the curse of Vyletongue\'s corruption, I will be able to assist you, if you\'d like to bring me the two parts -- both the head and the rod of the scepter.' WHERE entry=6385; /* Text0_0: Without knowledge of the incantations required to unite the two parts, Lord Vyletongue was unable to use the scepter. However, now that I am free of the curse of Vyletongue\'s corruption, I will be able to assist you, if you\'d like to bring me the two parts -- both the head and the rod of the scepter. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You ask of the Sons of Cenarius, Remulos and Zaetar.$B$BMy father, Remulos, was strong and beautiful, and my uncle, Zaetar, very cunning and slight of build. While they were respected quite equally, Zaetar always felt as if he could never quite compare to the glory and attention he thought Remulos had.$B$BAfter my sisters and I were born, Zaetar, blinded by jealousy, set out to outdo his brother... He was the creator of his own end. The sadness it brings me has never lessened, even as time passes...' WHERE entry=6393; /* Text0_0: You ask of the Sons of Cenarius, Remulos and Zaetar.$B$BMy father, Remulos, was strong and beautiful, and my uncle, Zaetar, very cunning and slight of build. While they were respected quite equally, Zaetar always felt as if he could never quite compare to the glory and attention he thought Remulos had.$B$BAfter my sisters and I were born, Zaetar, blinded by jealousy, set out to outdo his brother... He was the creator of his own end. The sadness it brings me has never lessened, even as time passes... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings, $N. I am Doctor Gregory Victor, head trauma surgeon of Horde Trauma.' WHERE entry=6413; /* Text0_0: Greetings, $N. I am Doctor Gregory Victor, head trauma surgeon of Horde Trauma. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='It is good to see you again, Doctor $N. I have been following your progress and I dare say that it is time you learned some of the more advanced bandaging techniques.$B$BReturn to me from time to time, as your skill advances, and I shall teach you all that I know.' WHERE entry=6414; /* Text0_0: It is good to see you again, Doctor $N. I have been following your progress and I dare say that it is time you learned some of the more advanced bandaging techniques.$B$BReturn to me from time to time, as your skill advances, and I shall teach you all that I know. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Greetings, $N. I am Doctor Gustaf VanHowzen, head trauma surgeon of Alliance Trauma.' WHERE entry=6415; /* Text0_0: Greetings, $N. I am Doctor Gustaf VanHowzen, head trauma surgeon of Alliance Trauma. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Hail, $N!  It is good you came to see me.  We are prepared to launch a ground assuault through the Field of Strife!  Once Warmaster Garrick gets his orders, he and his reavers will cut a swath through the Alliance!$B$BDo you want to deliver those orders, $N?  Garrick is waiting in the Field of Strife...' WHERE entry=6433; /* Text0_1: Hail, $N!  It is good you came to see me.  We are prepared to launch a ground assuault through the Field of Strife!  Once Warmaster Garrick gets his orders, he and his reavers will cut a swath through the Alliance!$B$BDo you want to deliver those orders, $N?  Garrick is waiting in the Field of Strife... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='It\'s good to have veterans like you in Alterac Valley, $N.  Our supplies are too low to launch a ground assault through Alterac Valley... speak with our quartermaster - he\'ll tell you how to increase our supply base.' WHERE entry=6435; /* Text0_1: It\'s good to have veterans like you in Alterac Valley, $N.  Our supplies are too low to launch a ground assault through Alterac Valley... speak with our quartermaster - he\'ll tell you how to increase our supply base. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='You!  $N!  What are you doing wandering around the village like this?  There are Alliance foes in Alterac!  We must drive them out!$B$BOur supplies are too low to launch a large ground assault, so speak with our quatermaster.  He\'ll tell you how you can increase our supply base.' WHERE entry=6437; /* Text0_1: You!  $N!  What are you doing wandering around the village like this?  There are Alliance foes in Alterac!  We must drive them out!$B$BOur supplies are too low to launch a large ground assault, so speak with our quatermaster.  He\'ll tell you how you can increase our supply base. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I am in charge of recruitment for the Frostwolf Clan. As a soldier of Frostwolf, it is your responsibility to check in with me as your rank among the clan rises.$B$BHonor and respect are earned on this frigid field.' WHERE entry=6475; /* Text0_0: I am in charge of recruitment for the Frostwolf Clan. As a soldier of Frostwolf, it is your responsibility to check in with me as your rank among the clan rises.$B$BHonor and respect are earned on this frigid field. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Hail, $r! I am Lieutenant Haggerdin, officer in charge of recruitment for the Stormpike Guard.$B$BAs you gain prestige and notoriety among the Stormpike, return to me and I shall see about upgrading your insignia. Also, should you ever lose your insignia, I am able to supply a replacement.' WHERE entry=6476; /* Text0_0: Hail, $r! I am Lieutenant Haggerdin, officer in charge of recruitment for the Stormpike Guard.$B$BAs you gain prestige and notoriety among the Stormpike, return to me and I shall see about upgrading your insignia. Also, should you ever lose your insignia, I am able to supply a replacement. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='It is not yet your time. I shall aid your journey back to the realm of the living... for a price.' WHERE entry=6491; /* Text0_0: It is not yet your time. I shall aid your journey back to the realm of the living... for a price. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Our ancestors teach us that while the individual must be strong, there is safety in numbers.  Do you wish to defend the honor of Thunder Bluff by organizing a guild?' WHERE entry=6513; /* Text0_0: Our ancestors teach us that while the individual must be strong, there is safety in numbers.  Do you wish to defend the honor of Thunder Bluff by organizing a guild? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Aye, you look the type to be a leader.  Here to organize a guild to fight for the Alliance?' WHERE entry=6514; /* Text0_0: Aye, you look the type to be a leader.  Here to organize a guild to fight for the Alliance? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well met, $c. I am Rokaro.' WHERE entry=6533; /* Text0_0: Well met, $c. I am Rokaro. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='What is it you ask of the Blue Flight?' WHERE entry=6534; /* Text0_1: What is it you ask of the Blue Flight? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Master Nesingwary has a big hunt ahead of him.  I find helping him prepare for a day in the jungle is much more relaxing than helping him ready for combat.  Although I do miss some of those glorious moments on the battlefield.' WHERE entry=6535; /* Text0_0: Master Nesingwary has a big hunt ahead of him.  I find helping him prepare for a day in the jungle is much more relaxing than helping him ready for combat.  Although I do miss some of those glorious moments on the battlefield. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='I know these forests as if they were a part of me... But know that there is still much to be learned from them, and much danger still hidden.' WHERE entry=6553; /* Text0_1: I know these forests as if they were a part of me... But know that there is still much to be learned from them, and much danger still hidden. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='You have completed Teronis\' mission, and I appreciate all you have done, $N.' WHERE entry=6555; /* Text0_1: You have completed Teronis\' mission, and I appreciate all you have done, $N. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Hiya! This workshop isn\'t mine, no! But one day after I finish training I am going to be an inventor, just like my hero, Marvon Rivetseeker.$B$BYou\'ve never heard of him? Well it just so happens that he left quite some time ago to study some ancient troll ruins he kept talking about. He left in a zeppelin... not quite sure about where exactly he went...$B$BTanarasin? Tenkeris? Taneranisany?$B$B<Liv shakes her head.>$B$BNo, that\'s not it...' WHERE entry=6556; /* Text0_1: Hiya! This workshop isn\'t mine, no! But one day after I finish training I am going to be an inventor, just like my hero, Marvon Rivetseeker.$B$BYou\'ve never heard of him? Well it just so happens that he left quite some time ago to study some ancient troll ruins he kept talking about. He left in a zeppelin... not quite sure about where exactly he went...$B$BTanarasin? Tenkeris? Taneranisany?$B$B<Liv shakes her head.>$B$BNo, that\'s not it... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Hi there. No, Marvon sure isn\'t here, and he won\'t be back for quite some time. Actually, I am getting a little worried about him...$B$BI hope he gets back soon. A large chest arrived for him and it\'s too heavy for me to lug it inside here! I had to leave it out by the door...' WHERE entry=6557; /* Text0_1: Hi there. No, Marvon sure isn\'t here, and he won\'t be back for quite some time. Actually, I am getting a little worried about him...$B$BI hope he gets back soon. A large chest arrived for him and it\'s too heavy for me to lug it inside here! I had to leave it out by the door... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You have learned all that I am able to teach you at this time, Doctor $N. Return to me when your practice has expanded and I shall train you in the ways of the more advanced medicinal arts.' WHERE entry=6573; /* Text0_0: You have learned all that I am able to teach you at this time, Doctor $N. Return to me when your practice has expanded and I shall train you in the ways of the more advanced medicinal arts. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='This place... it\'s cursed.$B$BI barely managed to escape, and I cannot bear to go down through the tunnels again.$B$BMy brother, and sisters though... They were not as fortunate. Trapped inside, they are feverish with the corrupted haze that flows from the evil garden growing there.$B$BPlease, you must help.' WHERE entry=6574; /* Text0_1: This place... it\'s cursed.$B$BI barely managed to escape, and I cannot bear to go down through the tunnels again.$B$BMy brother, and sisters though... They were not as fortunate. Trapped inside, they are feverish with the corrupted haze that flows from the evil garden growing there.$B$BPlease, you must help. */
