UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Around this reindeer\'s neck is a tag with the Smokywood Pastures logo on it and a name - "Metzen".$B$BMetzen looks at you with sad, forlorn eyes.  It is almost as if the reindeer has been immobilized by some unseen force.' WHERE entry=8076; /* Text0_0: Around this reindeer\'s neck is a tag with the Smokywood Pastures logo on it and a name - "Metzen".$B$BMetzen looks at you with sad, forlorn eyes.  It is almost as if the reindeer has been immobilized by some unseen force. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Metzen\'s eyes light up with reindeer joy as you sprinkle the dust on him.  He shakes his antlers at you and breathes out a heavy sigh of what sounds like relief.$B$BAround you, magical energy begins to swell.  It would seem that something\'s about to happen!' WHERE entry=8077; /* Text0_0: Metzen\'s eyes light up with reindeer joy as you sprinkle the dust on him.  He shakes his antlers at you and breathes out a heavy sigh of what sounds like relief.$B$BAround you, magical energy begins to swell.  It would seem that something\'s about to happen! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Even if you somehow managed to free us without defeating C\'Thun, we would focus all of our powers to see the beast banished back to the hell from whence it came - AT ANY COST.' WHERE entry=8078; /* Text0_0: Even if you somehow managed to free us without defeating C\'Thun, we would focus all of our powers to see the beast banished back to the hell from whence it came - AT ANY COST. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Heroes of the Brood? C\'Thun must be banished! We can assist you, mortal!' WHERE entry=8079; /* Text0_1: Heroes of the Brood? C\'Thun must be banished! We can assist you, mortal! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I bear witness to a miracle that stands before me! In one thousand years of captivity, I have not seen a single LIVING specimen - other than those foul Qiraji and silithid - enter these chambers.' WHERE entry=8080; /* Text0_0: I bear witness to a miracle that stands before me! In one thousand years of captivity, I have not seen a single LIVING specimen - other than those foul Qiraji and silithid - enter these chambers. */
