UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='These Runestones protect the lands in Eversong from becoming tainted by the Scourge.  The Western Runestone failed long ago, forcing us to burn the ground around it.$B$BAs long as I live I won\'t allow the remaining Runestones to fail us.  That is my oath.' WHERE entry=8504; /* Text0_0: These Runestones protect the lands in Eversong from becoming tainted by the Scourge.  The Western Runestone failed long ago, forcing us to burn the ground around it.$B$BAs long as I live I won\'t allow the remaining Runestones to fail us.  That is my oath. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Well, you didn\'t come all this way out here to jaw over a cup of tea. Let\'s see how you might be able to help get us out of this situation.' WHERE entry=8505; /* Text0_1: Well, you didn\'t come all this way out here to jaw over a cup of tea. Let\'s see how you might be able to help get us out of this situation. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Is this the best they could do?$B$B<Omarion musters the strength to laugh.>$B$BYou do not possess the resolve to face a monster like Kel\'Thuzad. You will crumble before his minions - just like those that have come before you...$B$BLeave me here to die. I refuse to return to a world that champions the likes of you.$B' WHERE entry=8507; /* Text0_1: Is this the best they could do?$B$B<Omarion musters the strength to laugh.>$B$BYou do not possess the resolve to face a monster like Kel\'Thuzad. You will crumble before his minions - just like those that have come before you...$B$BLeave me here to die. I refuse to return to a world that champions the likes of you.$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Master craftsman Omarion just vanished one night. Like a toot in the wind... Poof! Gone! Bah, now I\'m the only one left to craft the goods for the boys on the front lines. ' WHERE entry=8513; /* Text0_0: Master craftsman Omarion just vanished one night. Like a toot in the wind... Poof! Gone! Bah, now I\'m the only one left to craft the goods for the boys on the front lines. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Sin\'dorei and Forsaken share a common goal in the Ghostlands, $N.  Together we shall defeat the Scourge and who knows... perhaps the Forsaken will be valuable allies in our quest to reach Outland.' WHERE entry=8515; /* Text0_0: Sin\'dorei and Forsaken share a common goal in the Ghostlands, $N.  Together we shall defeat the Scourge and who knows... perhaps the Forsaken will be valuable allies in our quest to reach Outland. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='<Omarion grumbles something under his breath.>$B$BBut of course I can help you, dear $g boy:girl;. It is my dying wish... my final desire. Please, take this handbook. The information on its pages are a compilation of all that I know and have learned in the past 30 some-odd years of my miserable life. Give the handbook to that good for nothing apprentice of mine that\'s probably sitting on his fat duff at Light\'s Hope Chapel.' WHERE entry=8516; /* Text0_1: <Omarion grumbles something under his breath.>$B$BBut of course I can help you, dear $g boy:girl;. It is my dying wish... my final desire. Please, take this handbook. The information on its pages are a compilation of all that I know and have learned in the past 30 some-odd years of my miserable life. Give the handbook to that good for nothing apprentice of mine that\'s probably sitting on his fat duff at Light\'s Hope Chapel. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='<Tarsis groans.>$B$BThere may still be time... Listen closely, mortal.$B$BThrough time and across the Nether I have searched. Deals made with a host of evil and villainy so wretched...$B$B<Tarsis coughs blood into his hands.>$B$BWould you... would you believe that even Elune has turned her back on me, $r? To die here, in this manner now...' WHERE entry=8517; /* Text0_0: <Tarsis groans.>$B$BThere may still be time... Listen closely, mortal.$B$BThrough time and across the Nether I have searched. Deals made with a host of evil and villainy so wretched...$B$B<Tarsis coughs blood into his hands.>$B$BWould you... would you believe that even Elune has turned her back on me, $r? To die here, in this manner now... */
