UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='This is just horrible.$B$BI care not for our own discomforts here, but we must do something to ease the pain of the dead in the Bone Wastes!' WHERE entry=9477; /* Text0_0: This is just horrible.$B$BI care not for our own discomforts here, but we must do something to ease the pain of the dead in the Bone Wastes! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='You are here to assist the Aldor?' WHERE entry=9478; /* Text0_1: You are here to assist the Aldor? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If you\'re expecting some kind of official welcome, you\'re going to be disappointed, $c. We don\'t stand on tradition, here. What works is what goes.' WHERE entry=9481; /* Text0_0: If you\'re expecting some kind of official welcome, you\'re going to be disappointed, $c. We don\'t stand on tradition, here. What works is what goes. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='One note stands out from the other various pieces of parchment that are tacked onto this wanted poster.  It\'s a call to slay the bonelashers of the Bone Wastes.' WHERE entry=9482; /* Text0_0: One note stands out from the other various pieces of parchment that are tacked onto this wanted poster.  It\'s a call to slay the bonelashers of the Bone Wastes. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='No, don\'t feel bad.  I get that a lot.$B$B<Taela looks both amused and annoyed.>$B$BI\'m a HIGH elf, not a blood elf.  Don\'t worry, I\'m not going to suck all of the magic out of you.' WHERE entry=9484; /* Text0_1: No, don\'t feel bad.  I get that a lot.$B$B<Taela looks both amused and annoyed.>$B$BI\'m a HIGH elf, not a blood elf.  Don\'t worry, I\'m not going to suck all of the magic out of you. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Bonelashers, I hate them all!$B$BIf it weren\'t for the loss of my eye, and the fainting spells that I get sometimes, I\'d be out there shooting them down all the time!' WHERE entry=9485; /* Text0_0: Bonelashers, I hate them all!$B$BIf it weren\'t for the loss of my eye, and the fainting spells that I get sometimes, I\'d be out there shooting them down all the time! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I\'ve been watching the Aldor working on the walls. They\'re gonna rebuild the whole city, you know.$B$BThey work much faster than old Foreman Oslow did back home in Lakeshire. He kept losing his tools in the lake, or the gnolls would take his supplies.$B$BI should ask the Aldor to send him some help. They\'d have that bridge fixed faster\'n anything.' WHERE entry=9486; /* Text0_0: I\'ve been watching the Aldor working on the walls. They\'re gonna rebuild the whole city, you know.$B$BThey work much faster than old Foreman Oslow did back home in Lakeshire. He kept losing his tools in the lake, or the gnolls would take his supplies.$B$BI should ask the Aldor to send him some help. They\'d have that bridge fixed faster\'n anything. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='There\'s a whole vast forest out there, $c. Let the shaman play with the spirits and the warriors toy with their swords. Terokkar is where I\'ll make my fortune.' WHERE entry=9487; /* Text0_1: There\'s a whole vast forest out there, $c. Let the shaman play with the spirits and the warriors toy with their swords. Terokkar is where I\'ll make my fortune. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Malukaz chatters incessantly about the historical importance of this forest, but I don\'t have the luxury of indulging in history until our present problems are settled.$B$BI\'m not saying his work here isn\'t important, but someone has to see to the defenses and logistics of running the hold.' WHERE entry=9488; /* Text0_0: Malukaz chatters incessantly about the historical importance of this forest, but I don\'t have the luxury of indulging in history until our present problems are settled.$B$BI\'m not saying his work here isn\'t important, but someone has to see to the defenses and logistics of running the hold. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Until I traveled through Nagrand and came to the forest, I feared that too much of our original culture was lost. I\'m thankful to see that I was wrong.$B$BThere is so much to be done here!' WHERE entry=9489; /* Text0_0: Until I traveled through Nagrand and came to the forest, I feared that too much of our original culture was lost. I\'m thankful to see that I was wrong.$B$BThere is so much to be done here! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='The opening of the Dark Portal brought news of my people\'s fate. In a way, my exile shielded me from sharing in their downfall, but to see the Farstriders throw their lot in with Kael\'thas...$B$BI never imagined my one-time brethren capable of such a thing.$B$BThe homecoming I once dreamt of will never happen. This forest is the only home I have left.' WHERE entry=9490; /* Text0_1: The opening of the Dark Portal brought news of my people\'s fate. In a way, my exile shielded me from sharing in their downfall, but to see the Farstriders throw their lot in with Kael\'thas...$B$BI never imagined my one-time brethren capable of such a thing.$B$BThe homecoming I once dreamt of will never happen. This forest is the only home I have left. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='When I first arrived, I\'d hoped to meet the town\'s namesake.$B$B<Ros\'eleth glances around.>$B$BMost young high elves outgrow the \'I wanna be a Farstrider\' phase by the time they\'re taken as apprentices. Then, it\'s onto the \'I\'m going to be a magister\' stage.$B$BI don\'t think I ever quite outgrew the Farstrider phase, to be honest. No one dreams of growing up to be a seamstress, but we can\'t have the Farstriders running around naked, as my mother used to say.' WHERE entry=9492; /* Text0_1: When I first arrived, I\'d hoped to meet the town\'s namesake.$B$B<Ros\'eleth glances around.>$B$BMost young high elves outgrow the \'I wanna be a Farstrider\' phase by the time they\'re taken as apprentices. Then, it\'s onto the \'I\'m going to be a magister\' stage.$B$BI don\'t think I ever quite outgrew the Farstrider phase, to be honest. No one dreams of growing up to be a seamstress, but we can\'t have the Farstriders running around naked, as my mother used to say. */
