UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You should recieve a pack of incendiary bombs from Erozion before I fly you to Durnholde. You wouldn\'t want to waste time, after all.' WHERE entry=9780; /* Text0_0: You should recieve a pack of incendiary bombs from Erozion before I fly you to Durnholde. You wouldn\'t want to waste time, after all. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Horrible... just horrible!$B$BWe were minding our own business on our way from Area 52 in Netherstorm and they shot us down!  I knew we shouldn\'t have taken that shortcut to get to Terokkar Forest!' WHERE entry=9781; /* Text0_0: Horrible... just horrible!$B$BWe were minding our own business on our way from Area 52 in Netherstorm and they shot us down!  I knew we shouldn\'t have taken that shortcut to get to Terokkar Forest! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Expedition Point is the Alliance\'s closest point of contact with the Legion Front. North of here is nothin\' but demon, demon and more demon. Travel with a buddy.' WHERE entry=9784; /* Text0_0: Expedition Point is the Alliance\'s closest point of contact with the Legion Front. North of here is nothin\' but demon, demon and more demon. Travel with a buddy. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Illidari demons keep me here because of my knowledge of ancient draenei crystals and relics.$B$BThey\'ve enslaved many of my people and use us to look for a powerful crystal... one that in all likelihood is not even here.',Text0_1_loc9='The Illidari demons keep me here because of my knowledge of ancient draenei crystals and relics.$B$BThey\'ve enslaved many of my people and use us to look for a powerful crystal... one that in all likelihood is not even here.' WHERE entry=9787; /* Text0_0: The Illidari demons keep me here because of my knowledge of ancient draenei crystals and relics.$B$BThey\'ve enslaved many of my people and use us to look for a powerful crystal... one that in all likelihood is not even here. */ /* Text0_1: The Illidari demons keep me here because of my knowledge of ancient draenei crystals and relics.$B$BThey\'ve enslaved many of my people and use us to look for a powerful crystal... one that in all likelihood is not even here. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What for?  If Illidan\'s demons don\'t catch me and enslave me again, then the naga of Zangarmarsh will.$B$BJoining Illidan and his allies has turned out to mean nothing but slavery to most of the Broken tribes.  There is no hope for my people.',Text0_1_loc9='Why faire, moans illidari does not catch up with me, then it will be of the naga mark cage Zangar.  join  Illidan and his alli\'aura actually apport that slavery most tribes Rous. There is no hope for my people.' WHERE entry=9788; /* Text0_0: What for?  If Illidan\'s demons don\'t catch me and enslave me again, then the naga of Zangarmarsh will.$B$BJoining Illidan and his allies has turned out to mean nothing but slavery to most of the Broken tribes.  There is no hope for my people. */ /* Text0_1: Why faire, moans illidari does not catch up with me, then it will be of the naga mark cage Zangar.  join  Illidan and his alli\'aura actually apport that slavery most tribes Rous. There is no hope for my people. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I\'ll never take another shortcut again, I swear! How was I supposed to know the skies over Hellfire Peninsula were that dangerous?' WHERE entry=9789; /* Text0_0: I\'ll never take another shortcut again, I swear! How was I supposed to know the skies over Hellfire Peninsula were that dangerous? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='<A soothing light fills you as you approach the naaru.  Slow musical chimes echo within your mind and, though a word is not uttered, you feel an assurance of safety.  You are welcome in Shattrath City.>' WHERE entry=9800; /* Text0_0: <A soothing light fills you as you approach the naaru.  Slow musical chimes echo within your mind and, though a word is not uttered, you feel an assurance of safety.  You are welcome in Shattrath City.> */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Move along unless you\'ve got business with the fleet.' WHERE entry=9801; /* Text0_0: Move along unless you\'ve got business with the fleet. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='She\'s a beaut\', isn\'t she? Sky\'ree... the faithful gryphon of our commander. Kurdran himself, he holds his audiences in th\' stronghold. I care fer our Sky\'ree here when he\'s busy. Gorgeous creature, she is; as strong and fierce as they come. She\'d die fer Kurdran, she would. A more loyal soul ye\'ve ne\'er seen.\'Tis an honor to care fer her, it is.' WHERE entry=9805; /* Text0_0: She\'s a beaut\', isn\'t she? Sky\'ree... the faithful gryphon of our commander. Kurdran himself, he holds his audiences in th\' stronghold. I care fer our Sky\'ree here when he\'s busy. Gorgeous creature, she is; as strong and fierce as they come. She\'d die fer Kurdran, she would. A more loyal soul ye\'ve ne\'er seen.\'Tis an honor to care fer her, it is. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='What did Garrosh tell you, $N?' WHERE entry=9819; /* Text0_1: What did Garrosh tell you, $N? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='<Greatmother Geyah nods, accepting your answer.>$B$BI can no longer fight the spirits, $N. My time has long since passed. Once again, I must thank you for all that you have done. While Garrosh may be unmovable, many of my people have been lifted by your accomplishments. They are now willing to fight for our rights as a united clan.' WHERE entry=9821; /* Text0_1: <Greatmother Geyah nods, accepting your answer.>$B$BI can no longer fight the spirits, $N. My time has long since passed. Once again, I must thank you for all that you have done. While Garrosh may be unmovable, many of my people have been lifted by your accomplishments. They are now willing to fight for our rights as a united clan. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='<Greatmother Geyah smiles at you.>$B$BYou remind me of my son, $N.$B$BHe was an immovable mountain: A pillar of strength and honor.$B$B<Geyah\'s eyes well up with tears.>$B$BHe sacrificed himself so that we could survive. So that generations of orcs after him could be born into a world without the blood curse... Without Gul\'dan and his dark Horde...$B$B<Geyah stares into the distance, lost in thought.>$B$BOh Durotan, how I wish you could be here. Your people so desperately need you...' WHERE entry=9822; /* Text0_1: <Greatmother Geyah smiles at you.>$B$BYou remind me of my son, $N.$B$BHe was an immovable mountain: A pillar of strength and honor.$B$B<Geyah\'s eyes well up with tears.>$B$BHe sacrificed himself so that we could survive. So that generations of orcs after him could be born into a world without the blood curse... Without Gul\'dan and his dark Horde...$B$B<Geyah stares into the distance, lost in thought.>$B$BOh Durotan, how I wish you could be here. Your people so desperately need you... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='<Greatmother Geyah nods.>$B$BDid you know my son?' WHERE entry=9823; /* Text0_1: <Greatmother Geyah nods.>$B$BDid you know my son? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='<Greatmother Geyah\'s violet eyes lock onto yours.>$B$BYes...' WHERE entry=9824; /* Text0_1: <Greatmother Geyah\'s violet eyes lock onto yours.>$B$BYes... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='<Tears stream down Greatmother Geyah\'s face.>$B$BI... I... Durotan survived to have a child? The child Draka told me of before they left... It was their greatest fear... To raise a child in this world. On the other side of that gate was their only hope. I dared not tell Durotan, but secretly, I begged the spirits to watch over them - to protect their child and to give them strength.$B$BI... I must see my grandchild. I must see him. Please, I am too weak. You must tell him. Before I leave this world...$B$B' WHERE entry=9825; /* Text0_1: <Tears stream down Greatmother Geyah\'s face.>$B$BI... I... Durotan survived to have a child? The child Draka told me of before they left... It was their greatest fear... To raise a child in this world. On the other side of that gate was their only hope. I dared not tell Durotan, but secretly, I begged the spirits to watch over them - to protect their child and to give them strength.$B$BI... I must see my grandchild. I must see him. Please, I am too weak. You must tell him. Before I leave this world...$B$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='\'Netherstorm\' was not always as you see it now.$B$BThere was a time when this crumbling land was known as the Plains of Farahlon. Little of those days has survived the evil that has taken hold here.' WHERE entry=9826; /* Text0_0: \'Netherstorm\' was not always as you see it now.$B$BThere was a time when this crumbling land was known as the Plains of Farahlon. Little of those days has survived the evil that has taken hold here. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='$C, hold your attack, this is just a disguise!  I\'m a spy working for the Lower City coalition out of Shattrath City.$B$BI hope you\'re here to help!' WHERE entry=9827; /* Text0_1: $C, hold your attack, this is just a disguise!  I\'m a spy working for the Lower City coalition out of Shattrath City.$B$BI hope you\'re here to help! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Archmage Vargoth enstrusted me with his staff when he told me to flee from the blood elf attack on Violet Tower. I did as he told me, hoping to take refuge in the old draenei settlement of Arklon.$B$BThere was to be no respite. I had walked right into the leading edge of a Burning Legion force. The demons wrested the staff from me, but I managed to escape with my life.$B$BThough my master knows nothing of my failure, it still shames me.' WHERE entry=9828; /* Text0_0: Archmage Vargoth enstrusted me with his staff when he told me to flee from the blood elf attack on Violet Tower. I did as he told me, hoping to take refuge in the old draenei settlement of Arklon.$B$BThere was to be no respite. I had walked right into the leading edge of a Burning Legion force. The demons wrested the staff from me, but I managed to escape with my life.$B$BThough my master knows nothing of my failure, it still shames me. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Well. Look what the netherwinds swept in. Come in, sit down, and rest yourself a spell. The fee is modest; you can surely afford it.',Text0_1_loc9='Well. Look what the netherwinds swept in. Come in, sit down, and rest yourself a spell. The fee is modest; you can surely afford it.',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9832; /* Text0_0: Well. Look what the netherwinds swept in. Come in, sit down, and rest yourself a spell. The fee is modest; you can surely afford it. */ /* Text0_1: Well. Look what the netherwinds swept in. Come in, sit down, and rest yourself a spell. The fee is modest; you can surely afford it. */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Do they never rest?!$B$BIf we\'re to secure a future for the people of the Lower City, we must deal with the Shadow Council before they cause an even greater cataclysm than the Bone Wastes!$B$BBecause the leadership of Shattrath City will not move quickly, we the free people of the Lower City have taken matters into our own hands.$B$BBut our spies have been discovered.  We will hold off the Shadow Council\'s agents while you slip into the labyrinth and see what you can uncover.' WHERE entry=9833; /* Text0_0: Do they never rest?!$B$BIf we\'re to secure a future for the people of the Lower City, we must deal with the Shadow Council before they cause an even greater cataclysm than the Bone Wastes!$B$BBecause the leadership of Shattrath City will not move quickly, we the free people of the Lower City have taken matters into our own hands.$B$BBut our spies have been discovered.  We will hold off the Shadow Council\'s agents while you slip into the labyrinth and see what you can uncover. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Long ago, in a dimension of the cosmos unfathomable to mortal minds, there was born - if such a term can be used for it - a being of such unbelievable power that its very entrance into existence shattered all reality around it.$B$BKnown only as Murmur, it was the essence of sound, and to hear it speak was to know death eternal!' WHERE entry=9834; /* Text0_0: Long ago, in a dimension of the cosmos unfathomable to mortal minds, there was born - if such a term can be used for it - a being of such unbelievable power that its very entrance into existence shattered all reality around it.$B$BKnown only as Murmur, it was the essence of sound, and to hear it speak was to know death eternal! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Existing only for chaos, its slightest whisper meant the destruction of whole worlds!$B$BYet still, there were those that would try to worship this mindless being.  There were even those more insane who dared to think to control it!' WHERE entry=9835; /* Text0_0: Existing only for chaos, its slightest whisper meant the destruction of whole worlds!$B$BYet still, there were those that would try to worship this mindless being.  There were even those more insane who dared to think to control it! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The musty pages of the codex seem to magically turn themselves, guiding your attention to a specific chapter past horrors no mortal eyes should ever perceive.$B$BThe book opens to a page that somehow feels \'right,\' yet so very wrong.' WHERE entry=9836; /* Text0_0: The musty pages of the codex seem to magically turn themselves, guiding your attention to a specific chapter past horrors no mortal eyes should ever perceive.$B$BThe book opens to a page that somehow feels \'right,\' yet so very wrong. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='And lo, how the mighty fell trembling at its feet, fearful that it might direct its words upon them.$B$BBut still did these charlatans, these worshipping pretenders to a non-existent religion, rail against the inevitable in a vain attempt to control their \'god.\'  Uncaring, and likely not even noticing them, Murmur yawned and they knew oblivion.$B$BYet one somehow managed to survive, and in his insanity found a way to bring Murmur into the world.' WHERE entry=9837; /* Text0_0: And lo, how the mighty fell trembling at its feet, fearful that it might direct its words upon them.$B$BBut still did these charlatans, these worshipping pretenders to a non-existent religion, rail against the inevitable in a vain attempt to control their \'god.\'  Uncaring, and likely not even noticing them, Murmur yawned and they knew oblivion.$B$BYet one somehow managed to survive, and in his insanity found a way to bring Murmur into the world. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='A mortal possessed of arcane and dark knowledge that none could surpass, he devised a method to enhance his summoning through the capture and use of souls untold.$B$BWhole civilizations were brought to extinction through his soul devices to fuel the ritual through which he and his conspirators would bring Murmur into their world.' WHERE entry=9838; /* Text0_0: A mortal possessed of arcane and dark knowledge that none could surpass, he devised a method to enhance his summoning through the capture and use of souls untold.$B$BWhole civilizations were brought to extinction through his soul devices to fuel the ritual through which he and his conspirators would bring Murmur into their world. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='And summon forth Murmur they did.$B$BPowerful magics of containment and silencing were employed, held together by the constant supply of souls being fed into them.  Yet still they could not control the beast, could not bend it to their will.$B$BThese mortals began to devise different strategies, and one after the other they all failed.  And in so doing, they weakened the rituals, accidentally giving Murmur the slightest modicum of freedom.$B$BIt was all that was needed.' WHERE entry=9839; /* Text0_0: And summon forth Murmur they did.$B$BPowerful magics of containment and silencing were employed, held together by the constant supply of souls being fed into them.  Yet still they could not control the beast, could not bend it to their will.$B$BThese mortals began to devise different strategies, and one after the other they all failed.  And in so doing, they weakened the rituals, accidentally giving Murmur the slightest modicum of freedom.$B$BIt was all that was needed. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Only this book survived the cataclysm that destroyed their world. Those proud and foolish men who thought to control a cosmic being of untold power.$B$BWould you, the possessor of the codex, do the same?$B$BHave you devised a foolproof method to summon forth Murmur, or any of the other entities cautiously whispered of in these unhallowed pages?$B$BWe shall see.' WHERE entry=9840; /* Text0_0: Only this book survived the cataclysm that destroyed their world. Those proud and foolish men who thought to control a cosmic being of untold power.$B$BWould you, the possessor of the codex, do the same?$B$BHave you devised a foolproof method to summon forth Murmur, or any of the other entities cautiously whispered of in these unhallowed pages?$B$BWe shall see. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Hey there!  Good to see a new face - I don\'t get many visitors and the technicians aren\'t very good conversationalists.$B$BI bet you\'re on your way to Area 52.  Am I right?' WHERE entry=9841; /* Text0_0: Hey there!  Good to see a new face - I don\'t get many visitors and the technicians aren\'t very good conversationalists.$B$BI bet you\'re on your way to Area 52.  Am I right? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Rocket-Chief Fuselage, commander of B.O.O.M - the Braintrust of Orbital Operations and Mechanics - at your service.$B$BAre all systems go?!  It looks like the X-52 Nether-Rocket still needs a lot of work!$B$BCome on people... we\'re T-minus NEVER here!' WHERE entry=9844; /* Text0_0: Rocket-Chief Fuselage, commander of B.O.O.M - the Braintrust of Orbital Operations and Mechanics - at your service.$B$BAre all systems go?!  It looks like the X-52 Nether-Rocket still needs a lot of work!$B$BCome on people... we\'re T-minus NEVER here! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Welcome to the Allerian Stronghold, $N.' WHERE entry=9845; /* Text0_1: Welcome to the Allerian Stronghold, $N. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='This is delicate work out here, you know?  It can\'t just be rushed, or something\'s likely to get broken.$B$BLike Fuselage\'s head!$B$BYou might be wondering about my bots?  I\'m always working on the Mk. I, and the Mk. II gained sentience for a split-second before his brain capacitor blew out and he went insane!$B$BI decided to skip III and IV, and went straight to the Mk. V - my pride and joy!' WHERE entry=9846; /* Text0_1: This is delicate work out here, you know?  It can\'t just be rushed, or something\'s likely to get broken.$B$BLike Fuselage\'s head!$B$BYou might be wondering about my bots?  I\'m always working on the Mk. I, and the Mk. II gained sentience for a split-second before his brain capacitor blew out and he went insane!$B$BI decided to skip III and IV, and went straight to the Mk. V - my pride and joy! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Be careful among the ruins, $c. The Kirin Tor spirits you find there will not recognize you as a friend.$B$BThe custodian and I are the only ones whose spirits retained a strong enough tie to this place to preserve our full identities in death.' WHERE entry=9847; /* Text0_0: Be careful among the ruins, $c. The Kirin Tor spirits you find there will not recognize you as a friend.$B$BThe custodian and I are the only ones whose spirits retained a strong enough tie to this place to preserve our full identities in death. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Kirin\'Var survived 20 long years and countless orc assaults, but it could not withstand the forces of Kael\'thas. A man who once called himself a member of the Kirin Tor murdered all of us, save one.$B$BArchmage Vargoth survived the attack, so Kael\'thas imprisoned him within the Violet Tower, warding it with a magic that forbids the passage of any of the Kirin Tor.' WHERE entry=9848; /* Text0_0: Kirin\'Var survived 20 long years and countless orc assaults, but it could not withstand the forces of Kael\'thas. A man who once called himself a member of the Kirin Tor murdered all of us, save one.$B$BArchmage Vargoth survived the attack, so Kael\'thas imprisoned him within the Violet Tower, warding it with a magic that forbids the passage of any of the Kirin Tor. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You read wanted poster to Grek?$B$BGrek want to help!' WHERE entry=9853; /* Text0_0: You read wanted poster to Grek?$B$BGrek want to help! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Hello, what business brings you here?$B$BThis is an orphanage for the children of Outland who have lost their parents and have no one else to look after them.$B$BPerhaps you are here because you are considering adoption?' WHERE entry=9854; /* Text0_1: Hello, what business brings you here?$B$BThis is an orphanage for the children of Outland who have lost their parents and have no one else to look after them.$B$BPerhaps you are here because you are considering adoption? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What\'s your pleasure?  Pull up a seat and knock one back.$B$BI\'m Boots, lead mixologist for B.O.O.M. and bartender extraordinaire!$B$BIf it\'s got kick, Ol\' Boots can give it to ya.' WHERE entry=9863; /* Text0_0: What\'s your pleasure?  Pull up a seat and knock one back.$B$BI\'m Boots, lead mixologist for B.O.O.M. and bartender extraordinaire!$B$BIf it\'s got kick, Ol\' Boots can give it to ya. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Are you the correspondent from the Gadgetzan Times? If you just follow me, I\'ll show you my experimental apparatus...$B$B<You tell the magus that you\'re not the reporter she\'s expecting.>$B$BOh, you\'re not? Well then, if you need reagents, find what you need and don\'t tarry. I\'m expecting someone.' WHERE entry=9868; /* Text0_1: Are you the correspondent from the Gadgetzan Times? If you just follow me, I\'ll show you my experimental apparatus...$B$B<You tell the magus that you\'re not the reporter she\'s expecting.>$B$BOh, you\'re not? Well then, if you need reagents, find what you need and don\'t tarry. I\'m expecting someone. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Radiation?!$B$BNo, you don\'t need to worry about that!  Sheesh, the things that people believe these days.$B$BSo, what do you think of our operations down here?  State of the art, baby!  You better believe it.' WHERE entry=9869; /* Text0_0: Radiation?!$B$BNo, you don\'t need to worry about that!  Sheesh, the things that people believe these days.$B$BSo, what do you think of our operations down here?  State of the art, baby!  You better believe it. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='For years I was convinced we were doing the right thing in Silvermoon - working to reach Outland so we could be reunited with Kael.$B$BHad I known what Kael\'thas had in store for us, I would\'ve stayed right in Falconwing Square.' WHERE entry=9871; /* Text0_0: For years I was convinced we were doing the right thing in Silvermoon - working to reach Outland so we could be reunited with Kael.$B$BHad I known what Kael\'thas had in store for us, I would\'ve stayed right in Falconwing Square. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='There are two prominent bills tacked up on the board here; one from Papa Wheeler and one from Rocket-Chief Fuselage.$B$BPapa\'s looks like it\'s a wanted ad for a machine part.  The rocket-chief\'s has something to do with a bounty on the head of an immense mountain giant!$B$BThe details for both are provided in very small goblin handwriting, which is, of course, barely legible.' WHERE entry=9872; /* Text0_0: There are two prominent bills tacked up on the board here; one from Papa Wheeler and one from Rocket-Chief Fuselage.$B$BPapa\'s looks like it\'s a wanted ad for a machine part.  The rocket-chief\'s has something to do with a bounty on the head of an immense mountain giant!$B$BThe details for both are provided in very small goblin handwriting, which is, of course, barely legible. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='There are several prominent bills tacked up on the board here.$B$BHowever, the fine-print indicates that you\'re not quite ready for either of the tasks at hand.  You should definitely check back later!' WHERE entry=9873; /* Text0_0: There are several prominent bills tacked up on the board here.$B$BHowever, the fine-print indicates that you\'re not quite ready for either of the tasks at hand.  You should definitely check back later! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Shredders?!  They just won\'t cut it anymore.  They\'re so yesterday!$B$BIf we\'re going to build rockets - if we\'re going to get the X-52 off the ground - we need better tech!' WHERE entry=9875; /* Text0_0: Shredders?!  They just won\'t cut it anymore.  They\'re so yesterday!$B$BIf we\'re going to build rockets - if we\'re going to get the X-52 off the ground - we need better tech! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I am Khadgar, former apprentice to the fallen Guardian, Medivh. I\'m sure you\'ve heard his name before.$B$BIt was I who discovered that Medivh had been possessed by the Evil One, Sargeras - and that he had opened the Dark Portal between this world and Azeroth. Though I honored my Master, I was forced to slay him and put his tortured soul to rest.' WHERE entry=9876; /* Text0_0: I am Khadgar, former apprentice to the fallen Guardian, Medivh. I\'m sure you\'ve heard his name before.$B$BIt was I who discovered that Medivh had been possessed by the Evil One, Sargeras - and that he had opened the Dark Portal between this world and Azeroth. Though I honored my Master, I was forced to slay him and put his tortured soul to rest. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I fought alongside Lord Anduin Lothar as we drove the Horde from our lands on Azeroth. As the heir of Medivh\'s legacy, I could do no less.$B$BWhen the call finally came to invade this grim world - and put an end to the orcs\' evil forever - I stepped forward along with my friends Turalyon, Alleria, Danath and Kurdran.' WHERE entry=9877; /* Text0_0: I fought alongside Lord Anduin Lothar as we drove the Horde from our lands on Azeroth. As the heir of Medivh\'s legacy, I could do no less.$B$BWhen the call finally came to invade this grim world - and put an end to the orcs\' evil forever - I stepped forward along with my friends Turalyon, Alleria, Danath and Kurdran. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='My comrades and I called ourselves the Sons of Lothar - in honor of the greatest, most selfless man we ever knew.  We gave our all to defeat Ner\'zhul and end his madness.$B$BAs this doomed world fell apart around us, we shattered the Dark Portal to prevent any further harm befalling our beloved Azeroth.' WHERE entry=9878; /* Text0_0: My comrades and I called ourselves the Sons of Lothar - in honor of the greatest, most selfless man we ever knew.  We gave our all to defeat Ner\'zhul and end his madness.$B$BAs this doomed world fell apart around us, we shattered the Dark Portal to prevent any further harm befalling our beloved Azeroth. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Trapped in this broken wasteland, we did our best to survive. Over time we sensed that a new evil was closing in around us from the Twisting Nether.  More foul than the dark orcs - it was the Burning Legion itself that sought to take hold of this... Outland.' WHERE entry=9879; /* Text0_0: Trapped in this broken wasteland, we did our best to survive. Over time we sensed that a new evil was closing in around us from the Twisting Nether.  More foul than the dark orcs - it was the Burning Legion itself that sought to take hold of this... Outland. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='While my comrades held the line against the encroaching darkness, I used my magic to reach out into the Great Dark Beyond.  There, I sensed beings of immense Light - of unfathomable purity.$B$BIt was A\'dal and his naaru I had found. It was nothing short of a... miracle.' WHERE entry=9880; /* Text0_0: While my comrades held the line against the encroaching darkness, I used my magic to reach out into the Great Dark Beyond.  There, I sensed beings of immense Light - of unfathomable purity.$B$BIt was A\'dal and his naaru I had found. It was nothing short of a... miracle. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='<Khadgar grins to himself>$B$BI convinced A\'dal and his brethren to return here with me. I believe that only their power can drive the Legion from this universe. But as you will no doubt find - their power must first live in our hearts.$B$BTo combat the darkness, we must become beacons of their eternal Light.' WHERE entry=9881; /* Text0_0: <Khadgar grins to himself>$B$BI convinced A\'dal and his brethren to return here with me. I believe that only their power can drive the Legion from this universe. But as you will no doubt find - their power must first live in our hearts.$B$BTo combat the darkness, we must become beacons of their eternal Light. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What is it that you want, $r?' WHERE entry=9886; /* Text0_0: What is it that you want, $r? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What\'s an "Ologist?" A better question might be what isn\'t an "Ologist." It means I study everything! In fact, I\'m so well versed in "everything" that I\'m guaranteed to be the most intelligent ethereal you\'ll ever meet - or your money back.$B$BApologies. That\'s the dealer in me talking...' WHERE entry=9894; /* Text0_0: What\'s an "Ologist?" A better question might be what isn\'t an "Ologist." It means I study everything! In fact, I\'m so well versed in "everything" that I\'m guaranteed to be the most intelligent ethereal you\'ll ever meet - or your money back.$B$BApologies. That\'s the dealer in me talking... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='I\'m neither slim nor shady. As a matter of fact, I find both references insulting.$B$BNow, get out of my sight before I plant my staff up your backside.' WHERE entry=9895; /* Text0_0: I\'m neither slim nor shady. As a matter of fact, I find both references insulting.$B$BNow, get out of my sight before I plant my staff up your backside. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Ah, I see you are a friend to the Consortium. Perhaps you would be interested in making a purchase?' WHERE entry=9896; /* Text0_0: Ah, I see you are a friend to the Consortium. Perhaps you would be interested in making a purchase? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='That Shaffar is a clever bastard. He\'s rigged the entrance with some sort of ward to prevent other ethereal groups from entering. We\'re working on breaking through his defenses so we can get in there and take what\'s ours. I\'ve got top ethereals working on this around the clock. We\'ll have it open any minute now. I can feel it...' WHERE entry=9897; /* Text0_0: That Shaffar is a clever bastard. He\'s rigged the entrance with some sort of ward to prevent other ethereal groups from entering. We\'re working on breaking through his defenses so we can get in there and take what\'s ours. I\'ve got top ethereals working on this around the clock. We\'ll have it open any minute now. I can feel it... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The control panel shifts and rotates on its axis.' WHERE entry=9899; /* Text0_0: The control panel shifts and rotates on its axis. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='<The image\'s head blurs as it turns to take in its surroundings.>$B$BIf you had seen the Plains of Farahlon, you wouldn\'t believe this is the same place. Mere months ago, these fields would not have looked out of place in Westfall.$B$BAll that is gone now, but how and why?',Text1_0_loc9='The land is in worse shape than I could\'ve imagined. If the damage continues at this rate, Farahlon -- err, Netherstorm will be nothing but cosmic gravel very soon.$B$BWhere will it stop, I wonder? Perhaps the better question is, \'will it stop?\'' WHERE entry=9901; /* Text0_0: <The image\'s head blurs as it turns to take in its surroundings.>$B$BIf you had seen the Plains of Farahlon, you wouldn\'t believe this is the same place. Mere months ago, these fields would not have looked out of place in Westfall.$B$BAll that is gone now, but how and why? */ /* Text1_0: The land is in worse shape than I could\'ve imagined. If the damage continues at this rate, Farahlon -- err, Netherstorm will be nothing but cosmic gravel very soon.$B$BWhere will it stop, I wonder? Perhaps the better question is, \'will it stop?\' */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text2_0_loc9='<The archmage\'s image seems to look through you, rather than at you.>$B$BRibbons and currents of arcane energy ebb and flow here as if the area is awash in a sea of magical power. Not even the first cataclysm caused this kind of damage.',Text3_0_loc9='I will have my revenge on Kael\'thas for this outrage against the Kirin Tor! He once walked among us as a brother, but we are brothers no more.$B$BThere will be a reckoning.$B$B<The archmage nods grimly, not relishing the prospect.>$B$BKael\'thas is more than a mere rogue mage. Once I am free from my tower, Ravandwyr and I will assist anyone who opposes him.' WHERE entry=9901; /* Text2_0: <The archmage\'s image seems to look through you, rather than at you.>$B$BRibbons and currents of arcane energy ebb and flow here as if the area is awash in a sea of magical power. Not even the first cataclysm caused this kind of damage. */ /* Text3_0: I will have my revenge on Kael\'thas for this outrage against the Kirin Tor! He once walked among us as a brother, but we are brothers no more.$B$BThere will be a reckoning.$B$B<The archmage nods grimly, not relishing the prospect.>$B$BKael\'thas is more than a mere rogue mage. Once I am free from my tower, Ravandwyr and I will assist anyone who opposes him. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The orb behind me was once capable of glimpsing into the happenings on Azeroth.$B$BKael\'thas\'s curse changed all that, of course, but during our years of isolation many of the mages found solace in its images.$B$BSome scried to remember; some scried to forget. ',Text1_0_loc9='<Archmage Vargoth favors you with a wry smile.>$B$BPlenty of room at the cursed Violet Tower.$B$BAny time of year, you can find me here.' WHERE entry=9902; /* Text0_0: The orb behind me was once capable of glimpsing into the happenings on Azeroth.$B$BKael\'thas\'s curse changed all that, of course, but during our years of isolation many of the mages found solace in its images.$B$BSome scried to remember; some scried to forget. */ /* Text1_0: <Archmage Vargoth favors you with a wry smile.>$B$BPlenty of room at the cursed Violet Tower.$B$BAny time of year, you can find me here. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text2_0_loc9='The night Kael\'thas leveled the village, I could do nothing to help. His magic had already sealed me in the tower, exacerbating my torment by forcing me to witness the deaths of my fellows.$B$BAnd still their voices are calling from far away, waking me up in the middle of the night. ' WHERE entry=9902; /* Text2_0: The night Kael\'thas leveled the village, I could do nothing to help. His magic had already sealed me in the tower, exacerbating my torment by forcing me to witness the deaths of my fellows.$B$BAnd still their voices are calling from far away, waking me up in the middle of the night. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If you\'ve been sent to kill me, please take a number and wait your turn.' WHERE entry=9903; /* Text0_0: If you\'ve been sent to kill me, please take a number and wait your turn. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Keep it down!  I don\'t want them to see me over here.$B$BOoh, this really burns me up!  Who do these ethereals think they are?$B$BThis is MY claim!',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9904; /* Text0_0: Keep it down!  I don\'t want them to see me over here.$B$BOoh, this really burns me up!  Who do these ethereals think they are?$B$BThis is MY claim! */ /* Text0_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text0: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Please leave me to my sadness.' WHERE entry=9905; /* Text0_1: Please leave me to my sadness. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='That child gives me chills. He stands there all day long communing with his grandfather. He\'ll then turn to tell his mother what the grandfather told him and she - of course - just smiles and nods her head.$B$BLambs! Lemmings! All of them!$B' WHERE entry=9914; /* Text0_0: That child gives me chills. He stands there all day long communing with his grandfather. He\'ll then turn to tell his mother what the grandfather told him and she - of course - just smiles and nods her head.$B$BLambs! Lemmings! All of them!$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='When Rocket-Chief Fuselage was asking for volunteers to help out with building the X-52 Nether-Rocket, I submitted my resume for the security division.$B$BUnfortunately, the only position that was left was chief engineer.  Lucky for me, I have Xyrol here to look over my shoulder.' WHERE entry=9916; /* Text0_0: When Rocket-Chief Fuselage was asking for volunteers to help out with building the X-52 Nether-Rocket, I submitted my resume for the security division.$B$BUnfortunately, the only position that was left was chief engineer.  Lucky for me, I have Xyrol here to look over my shoulder. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Welcome, friend of the free people of the Lower City, but do not tarry long.$B$BThere are sounds of battle coming from within.  My compatriots could use your assistance!' WHERE entry=9917; /* Text0_0: Welcome, friend of the free people of the Lower City, but do not tarry long.$B$BThere are sounds of battle coming from within.  My compatriots could use your assistance! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='If you become a friend of the Lower City, perhaps we can do business?' WHERE entry=9918; /* Text0_0: If you become a friend of the Lower City, perhaps we can do business? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Can you believe this ethereal technology?!$B$BI\'m sure glad they let me stay out here with them.  I\'m gonna learn a lot... and maybe get some of it for myself, too!' WHERE entry=9919; /* Text0_1: Can you believe this ethereal technology?!$B$BI\'m sure glad they let me stay out here with them.  I\'m gonna learn a lot... and maybe get some of it for myself, too! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Beat it, kid. I got business to attend to...' WHERE entry=9920; /* Text0_0: Beat it, kid. I got business to attend to... */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='It is said that those who are blessed by the spirits of Auchindoun possess the ability to capture powerful souls in the form of Spirit Shards. I have come across a few of these Spirit Shards throughout my travels but have yet to unlock their secrets. $B$BThe only thing I have been able to discern is that they seem to originate from the depths of Auchindoun itself. If you happen to come across any of these Spirit Shards I\'m sure I could make it worth your while to allow me to take them off your hands...',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9921; /* Text0_0: It is said that those who are blessed by the spirits of Auchindoun possess the ability to capture powerful souls in the form of Spirit Shards. I have come across a few of these Spirit Shards throughout my travels but have yet to unlock their secrets. $B$BThe only thing I have been able to discern is that they seem to originate from the depths of Auchindoun itself. If you happen to come across any of these Spirit Shards I\'m sure I could make it worth your while to allow me to take them off your hands... */ /* Text0_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text0: */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='This crystal-based construct hums with energy.  Strange glyphs are projected in front of you and scroll in rapid succession.' WHERE entry=9922; /* Text0_0: This crystal-based construct hums with energy.  Strange glyphs are projected in front of you and scroll in rapid succession. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Busy, busy!  So much to do, so little time!$B$BNow where did I put that pyrospanner?  I know it\'s around here somewhere... I burned my fingers on it just a moment ago!' WHERE entry=9923; /* Text0_0: Busy, busy!  So much to do, so little time!$B$BNow where did I put that pyrospanner?  I know it\'s around here somewhere... I burned my fingers on it just a moment ago! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Knowing a little magic comes in handy in this line of work.  Illusions can\'t always fool everyone, but they\'re usually good enough to get the job done.' WHERE entry=9925; /* Text0_0: Knowing a little magic comes in handy in this line of work.  Illusions can\'t always fool everyone, but they\'re usually good enough to get the job done. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='What are you doing here?  Shouldn\'t you be working on the energy pipeline?$B$BWe\'ve more than doubled the amount of energy we\'re sending to Tempest Keep and can\'t afford anyone loafing.  We don\'t want another Ultris to happen here.' WHERE entry=9926; /* Text0_0: What are you doing here?  Shouldn\'t you be working on the energy pipeline?$B$BWe\'ve more than doubled the amount of energy we\'re sending to Tempest Keep and can\'t afford anyone loafing.  We don\'t want another Ultris to happen here. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Manaforge Ultris, of course!  Where have you been?$B$BThe manaforge was overloaded and created a huge explosion.  It left a tear in reality and now void creatures have been pouring in through it.  You can see them all over the place towards the northeast.' WHERE entry=9927; /* Text0_0: Manaforge Ultris, of course!  Where have you been?$B$BThe manaforge was overloaded and created a huge explosion.  It left a tear in reality and now void creatures have been pouring in through it.  You can see them all over the place towards the northeast. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='You ought to feel safe here; we\'ve stepped up security at this facility after the attacks on Manaforge Duro.' WHERE entry=9929; /* Text0_0: You ought to feel safe here; we\'ve stepped up security at this facility after the attacks on Manaforge Duro. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Manaforge Duro is the closest facility to Tempest Keep, so it handles most of the load.$B$BAs you should know, overloading these manaforges causes leaks in the pipelines.  The emanating energy attracts unwanted mana creatures.  We\'ve had mana creature infestations at many leak locations; Manaforge Duro is being hit the hardest at the moment.' WHERE entry=9930; /* Text0_0: Manaforge Duro is the closest facility to Tempest Keep, so it handles most of the load.$B$BAs you should know, overloading these manaforges causes leaks in the pipelines.  The emanating energy attracts unwanted mana creatures.  We\'ve had mana creature infestations at many leak locations; Manaforge Duro is being hit the hardest at the moment. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Working with this technology is a huge headache.  Everything is constructed in such an alien way.' WHERE entry=9931; /* Text0_1: Working with this technology is a huge headache.  Everything is constructed in such an alien way. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Many years ago, my men and I followed the wizard Khadgar and the paladin Turalyon to this world. Our sole aim was to annihilate the orcs and their vile kin. Yet something went terribly wrong in the final hours of our war.$B$BUltimately, this dark world was ripped asunder - and my dear friends were lost to the void.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9932; /* Text0_0: Many years ago, my men and I followed the wizard Khadgar and the paladin Turalyon to this world. Our sole aim was to annihilate the orcs and their vile kin. Yet something went terribly wrong in the final hours of our war.$B$BUltimately, this dark world was ripped asunder - and my dear friends were lost to the void. */ /* Text0_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text0: */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='We, the Sons of Lothar, have remained here ever since - fighting... dying... praying that a day like today would come - a day when the Portal would open and our brothers would come to deliver us home.$B$BOverjoyed as we are, duty still calls. There is much to be done before we can depart this world and take our rest.$B' WHERE entry=9933; /* Text0_0: We, the Sons of Lothar, have remained here ever since - fighting... dying... praying that a day like today would come - a day when the Portal would open and our brothers would come to deliver us home.$B$BOverjoyed as we are, duty still calls. There is much to be done before we can depart this world and take our rest.$B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_1_loc9='Don\'t they teach you new recruits anything?  These manaforges were built from parts of Tempest Keep designed to siphon energy from the nether.$B$BThe naaru used this technology to power their vessel during its travels.  Some said the technology might not be safe to use on land.  They were promptly silenced.' WHERE entry=9934; /* Text0_1: Don\'t they teach you new recruits anything?  These manaforges were built from parts of Tempest Keep designed to siphon energy from the nether.$B$BThe naaru used this technology to power their vessel during its travels.  Some said the technology might not be safe to use on land.  They were promptly silenced. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Another soldier on $ghis:her; way to Honor Hold... by Kurdran\'s beard, they can use the help!',Text0_1_loc9='Another soldier on $ghis:her; way to Honor Hold... by Kurdran\'s beard, they can use the help!' WHERE entry=9935; /* Text0_0: Another soldier on $ghis:her; way to Honor Hold... by Kurdran\'s beard, they can use the help! */ /* Text0_1: Another soldier on $ghis:her; way to Honor Hold... by Kurdran\'s beard, they can use the help! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:Доспехи – моя страсть! Меня хлебом не корми – дай починить что-нибудь! После смерти ничего не изменилось, так что представь, что перед тобой вполне живой дреней, $gнезнакомец:незнакомка;. Позволь мне вспомнить, каково это – жить… И окажи мне честь починить твои доспехи.',Text0_1_loc9='It\'s my passion, you know. In life and in death, armorcrafting is what I love. Please, treat me as if I were a living draenei, stranger. Let me know what it is to feel again... Allow me the honor of repairing your items.' WHERE entry=9936; /* Text0_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text0:Доспехи – моя страсть! Меня хлебом не корми – дай починить что-нибудь! После смерти ничего не изменилось, так что представь, что перед тобой вполне живой дреней, $gнезнакомец:незнакомка;. Позволь мне вспомнить, каково это – жить… И окажи мне честь починить твои доспехи. */ /* Text0_1: It\'s my passion, you know. In life and in death, armorcrafting is what I love. Please, treat me as if I were a living draenei, stranger. Let me know what it is to feel again... Allow me the honor of repairing your items. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The Consortium will exact its revenge upon the Zaxxis betrayers!' WHERE entry=9937; /* Text0_0: The Consortium will exact its revenge upon the Zaxxis betrayers! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Ah, a new champion to aid our cause? What say you, $N? $B',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9938; /* Text0_0: Ah, a new champion to aid our cause? What say you, $N? $B */ /* Text0_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text0: */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='$N, the Sons of Lothar have fought here, on the Hellfire Peninsula, for two decades.  We are beset on all sides by indigenous orcs and hellish demons of the Burning Crusade, and though our hearts still beat fiercely, years of war have reduced our numbers.$B$BYou, and the influx of Azeroth\'s new generation of heroes, are a welcome sight indeed!' WHERE entry=9939; /* Text0_0: $N, the Sons of Lothar have fought here, on the Hellfire Peninsula, for two decades.  We are beset on all sides by indigenous orcs and hellish demons of the Burning Crusade, and though our hearts still beat fiercely, years of war have reduced our numbers.$B$BYou, and the influx of Azeroth\'s new generation of heroes, are a welcome sight indeed! */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Orcs. It seems I\'ve been fighting them all my life.$B$BTwenty years ago we shattered the Horde and tore down the walls of their Hellfire Citadel. We drove the vile greenskins to the very brink! After that, other than a few skirmishes the broken orcs never again posed a threat to us.$B$BUntil now. $B' WHERE entry=9941; /* Text0_0: Orcs. It seems I\'ve been fighting them all my life.$B$BTwenty years ago we shattered the Horde and tore down the walls of their Hellfire Citadel. We drove the vile greenskins to the very brink! After that, other than a few skirmishes the broken orcs never again posed a threat to us.$B$BUntil now. $B */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='About twenty years ago, the Alliance launched the first Expedition to this world in hopes of eradicating the orcs forever. It was a... terrible conflict. Many brave souls perished to assure Azeroth\'s safety.$B$BYet some souls remain...locked in eternal combat.',Text0_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:',Text1_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:',Text1_1_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text1:' WHERE entry=9942; /* Text0_0: About twenty years ago, the Alliance launched the first Expedition to this world in hopes of eradicating the orcs forever. It was a... terrible conflict. Many brave souls perished to assure Azeroth\'s safety.$B$BYet some souls remain...locked in eternal combat. */ /* Text0_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text0: */ /* Text1_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */ /* Text1_1: MISSING ENGLISH Text1: */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='The men and women of Honor Hold have shed such blood and have lost their youth in this monstrous land... and yet they still hold their spirits high!$B$BNow, you and your cohorts from Azeroth can help us turn the tide.  You give us hope that we may one day return to our homelands.' WHERE entry=9944; /* Text0_0: The men and women of Honor Hold have shed such blood and have lost their youth in this monstrous land... and yet they still hold their spirits high!$B$BNow, you and your cohorts from Azeroth can help us turn the tide.  You give us hope that we may one day return to our homelands. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='As a representative of the Consortium, I am always mindful of the ramifications that my interactions have upon our business dealings.$B$BIt is unfortunate that the blood elves do not treat their partnerships with such respect.' WHERE entry=9947; /* Text0_0: As a representative of the Consortium, I am always mindful of the ramifications that my interactions have upon our business dealings.$B$BIt is unfortunate that the blood elves do not treat their partnerships with such respect. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='My younger brother here is quite the rising star in the Consortium. Of course, he\'s too modest to acknowledge it.' WHERE entry=9948; /* Text0_0: My younger brother here is quite the rising star in the Consortium. Of course, he\'s too modest to acknowledge it. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='MISSING ENGLISH Text0:Когда он говорит "младший брат", то забывает добавить, что мы близнецы. Он и старше-то всего на пару минут.$B$BТак что не дайте этой "восходящей звезде" обмануть вас. Я никогда не буду таким торговцем, как он.',Text0_1_loc9='When he says, \'younger brother,\' he fails to mention that we\'re twins. He\'s really only older by a couple of minutes.$B$BDon\'t let that \'rising star\' bit of his fool you. I\'ll never be a trader of the same magnitude that he is.' WHERE entry=9949; /* Text0_0: MISSING ENGLISH Text0:Когда он говорит "младший брат", то забывает добавить, что мы близнецы. Он и старше-то всего на пару минут.$B$BТак что не дайте этой "восходящей звезде" обмануть вас. Я никогда не буду таким торговцем, как он. */ /* Text0_1: When he says, \'younger brother,\' he fails to mention that we\'re twins. He\'s really only older by a couple of minutes.$B$BDon\'t let that \'rising star\' bit of his fool you. I\'ll never be a trader of the same magnitude that he is. */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='Hail to you, $r. What I am doing here is a story for another time. Oof, that was a bad one.$B$BMy brother and I are stuck here, between our time and the present. We dare not leave for fear of causing a temporal paradox. Patiently we wait until the dragons restore us to our proper timeline.$B$BHow long has it been you ask? I\'m not sure really. Ask my brother.$B$BCare for some cheese?' WHERE entry=9951; /* Text0_0: Hail to you, $r. What I am doing here is a story for another time. Oof, that was a bad one.$B$BMy brother and I are stuck here, between our time and the present. We dare not leave for fear of causing a temporal paradox. Patiently we wait until the dragons restore us to our proper timeline.$B$BHow long has it been you ask? I\'m not sure really. Ask my brother.$B$BCare for some cheese? */
UPDATE locales_npc_text SET Text0_0_loc9='No, you aren\'t hearing things. I actually do have the voice of a young orc woman. But you listen here, $g boy:girl;, time travel does strange things to a body.$B$BBy the way, it\'s 250 years.' WHERE entry=9953; /* Text0_0: No, you aren\'t hearing things. I actually do have the voice of a young orc woman. But you listen here, $g boy:girl;, time travel does strange things to a body.$B$BBy the way, it\'s 250 years. */
